Hell yes! Let's build this incident out with that JJK-style power system energy:
________________________________________
THE INCIDENT - "The Fracture" (or whatever you want to call it):
Something catastrophic happens in the city—could be:
•	A massive explosion at a research facility
•	A dimensional rift/tear in reality
•	A terrorist attack with unknown energy weapon
•	Strange meteor/phenomenon
The Aftermath:
•	Small percentage of people in the affected zone survive but are changed
•	Their internal conflicts, fears, desires literally manifest as abilities
•	The stronger your internal struggle, the stronger your power (but also the more unstable you are)
•	Most people got minor abilities; some got nothing; a few got dangerously powerful
For Your Protagonist: His constant internal battle between restraint and rage literally split him in two—and both sides got abilities that reflect their nature:
HOST's Abilities (Defensive/Tactical):
•	"Overthink" - Can process multiple scenarios simultaneously, predict patterns, see outcomes before acting (like a budget Gojo's Six Eyes mixed with anxiety)
•	Maybe time seems to slow when he's analyzing (but only for him mentally)
•	Defensive barriers or redirection based on "thinking through" attacks
•	Downside: Paralysis by analysis—can get stuck in his own head during critical moments
THE OTHER's Abilities (Offensive/Instinctive):
•	"No Hesitation" - Pure raw power, overwhelming offense, doesn't strategize just acts
•	Maybe enhanced physical abilities, destructive energy output, berserker-style combat
•	Abilities that get stronger the more reckless he is
•	Doesn't feel pain the same way, pure adrenaline combat
•	Downside: Burns through stamina, leaves Host's body wrecked
The Synergy (This is key for JJK vibes):
•	When they work together through the Bet System, they're unstoppable
•	Host analyzes the fight, Other executes perfectly
•	But this requires trust and cooperation—which they DON'T have early on
•	Creates growth arc where they learn to function as a unit
________________________________________
WIDER WORLD IMPLICATIONS:
New Power Hierarchy:
•	Government/organizations trying to register and control powered individuals
•	Underground fighting rings for powered people (cash and reputation—perfect for "making it big")
•	Some people became monsters (their darkness consumed them entirely)
•	Heroes, villains, and everyone in between navigating this new world
Potential Antagonists:
•	Someone whose inner conflict manifested as multiple external bodies (opposite problem—spread too thin)
•	A person with no internal conflict who got insane unified power (thinks they're chosen/superior)
•	Other dual-personality cases who merged successfully and look down on your MC for being "incomplete"
•	Someone whose power is to amplify internal conflicts in others (could force the switch)
The "Making It Big" Goal Gets Real Stakes:
•	Now it's not just about fame—powered individuals are the new elite
•	Top tier fighters/users get wealth, influence, protection
•	Staying weak or unknown means being prey
•	Both Host and Other want to climb this new hierarchy, but disagree on how
________________________________________
STORY HOOK:
Host has been trying to lay low since The Fracture, terrified of his Other. But rent's due, he's broke, and he hears about an underground tournament where powered people fight for cash prizes and reputation.
He knows he shouldn't go.
He knows this is exactly the kind of reckless thing that could spiral.
But the Other whispers: "You want to matter, right? Then stop being a coward and let's take what's ours."
And for the first time... Host agrees.
Failure Clause triggers—but this time, by choice.
________________________________________
Does this framework work? Want me to drill deeper into the power mechanics, the city's new status quo, or potential story arcs?
