we need a world building , i mean all these powers are good -- we need the incident to be better maybe it could be from the potential fight incident which was super intense between two people and the impact energy hit the area he lived in..
OH SHIT, YES! That's way better! Let me cook with this:
________________________________________
THE INCIDENT - "The Collision"
What Happened:
Two immensely powerful beings—let's call them Titans or Primals or whatever fits your vibe—had a catastrophic fight above/in the city.
The Setup:
•	These weren't normal people. Ancient? Supernatural? First generation of powered beings? Up to you.
•	Their fight was apocalyptic—think Gojo vs Sukuna level destruction, or Makima's final battle scale
•	They were evenly matched, fighting for [insert reason: ideology, territory, revenge, ancient grudge]
•	The fight reached a critical point where both unleashed their ultimate attacks simultaneously
The Collision: When their powers clashed, it created a shockwave of raw, unfiltered energy—not an explosion, but a wave of pure concept and willpower that washed over multiple city blocks.
The Effect - "Soul Fracture":
•	Everyone caught in the wave had their inner self exposed and shattered
•	Your deepest conflict, fear, desire, rage—all of it got ripped to the surface
•	For most people: trauma, nightmares, maybe minor sensory abilities
•	For those with intense internal struggles: their psyche literally broke and reformed into powers
•	The stronger your internal war, the more powerful (and unstable) you became
The Aftermath:
•	Both fighters? Gone. Disintegrated, disappeared, or merged with the energy—no one knows
•	The zone is called "The Scar" or "Ground Zero" or "The Broken District"
•	Thousands dead, thousands changed, the area is partially quarantined
•	Some buildings still have reality distortions, lingering energy
________________________________________
WORLD BUILDING - POST-COLLISION:
Three Years Later (or whatever timeline):
The Changed Ones (People with powers):
Tiers/Categories:
1.	Echoes (Majority - 60%) 
o	Barely affected, minor sensory enhancements or weird quirks
o	Can sense emotions, have better reflexes, minor elemental affinity
o	Basically normal people with tiny perks
2.	Fractured (Your MC's tier - 30%) 
o	Significant internal conflict manifested as real abilities
o	Range from street-level to seriously dangerous
o	Most have drawbacks, conditions, or instability
o	This is where the variety lives: combat powers, manipulation, transformation
3.	Shattered (Rare - 8%) 
o	Completely consumed by their manifestation
o	Became monsters, lost humanity, or split into separate entities
o	Extremely dangerous, usually contained or killed
o	Some retain intelligence but are fundamentally wrong now
4.	Reforged (Ultra-rare - 2%) 
o	Those who had internal conflict but resolved it during the Collision
o	Unified, stable, overwhelmingly powerful
o	These are the new apex predators of society
o	Think Special Grade level threats
Society's Response:
The Government/Authority:
•	Created The Registry - mandatory documentation of abilities (many refuse)
•	Containment Corps - specialized military for handling Shattered-class threats
•	Sanctuary Zones - "safe" districts with ability suppressors and heavy security
•	Debates rage: are Changed Ones victims or threats? Citizens or weapons?
The Underground:
•	The Pits - illegal fighting rings where Fractured battle for cash, rep, and territory
•	The Market - black market for ability enhancement drugs, stolen tech, contracts
•	Factions - gangs and groups organized by ability type or philosophy 
o	The Unified - Reforged supremacists who think Fractured are "incomplete"
o	The Originals - conspiracy theorists trying to find/resurrect the two fighters
o	The Unchained - anarchists who want to tear down the new power structure
Opportunity & Exploitation:
•	Changed Ones are the new celebrities, soldiers, criminals, and victims
•	Private military companies hire them
•	Entertainment industry exploits them (sanctioned fights, reality shows)
•	Some become heroes, most just try to survive
•	The Climb - informal ranking system in the underground (this is where "making it big" happens)
________________________________________
YOUR MC IN THIS WORLD:
His Collision Experience:
He was 18 when it happened. Home alone, paralyzed by indecision about his future, fighting with his own thoughts about what kind of person he wanted to be.
The wave hit.
His internal argument—safety vs ambition, restraint vs rage—was so intense that instead of manifesting as a single ability, it split him.
The voice that always criticized him, pushed him, demanded more? It became real.
His Current Situation (Age 21):
•	Been hiding the full extent of his condition (pretends to be a low-tier Fractured)
•	Working dead-end jobs, barely scraping by in The Scar district
•	The Other keeps pushing him to enter The Pits and climb the rankings
•	Host is terrified of what happens if they get noticed by the wrong people
•	But they're running out of time—something's brewing in the city, and staying invisible is becoming impossible
________________________________________
THE FIGHTERS (Mystery/Lore):
Keep them mysterious but present:
•	Codenames: Maybe "The Sovereign" and "The Revolutionary" or something thematic
•	Cult Following: People worship them, fear them, study recordings of the fight
•	Lingering Presence: Some believe they're not truly dead—that fragments of them exist in those Changed by the Collision
•	The Conspiracy: What if the fight was intentional? What if they wanted to create Changed Ones?
Potential Plot Thread: What if the Reforged are trying to collect/absorb other Changed Ones to reconstitute one (or both) of the original fighters? What if Host and Other are a particularly valuable piece because they're a perfect split?
________________________________________
Does this world feel lived-in enough? Want me to develop specific factions, flesh out The Pits, or create potential rival characters?
