PERFECT! Let me rebuild this:
________________________________________
THE WORLD - BEFORE THE COLLISION
Central Theme/Energy System: "RESOLVE"
What is Resolve?
•	The fundamental force of willpower, conviction, and inner strength that exists in all humans
•	Most people have weak, scattered Resolve—they live without true purpose or direction
•	Strong Resolve manifests as tangible power in rare individuals
•	It's not just "wanting something"—it's the unshakeable certainty that you will achieve it, consequences be damned
How It Works:
•	Your Resolve crystallizes based on your core drive/obsession
•	The more singular and intense your purpose, the stronger your abilities
•	Conflict weakens Resolve - doubt, hesitation, internal contradictions make you vulnerable
•	This is why most powerful people seem almost insane—they've eliminated all doubt
Before The Collision:
•	Maybe 0.001% of humanity naturally awakened Resolve abilities
•	These individuals were the hidden movers of society: assassins, cult leaders, corporate tyrants, warlords
•	Governments knew about them, had secret programs, tried to replicate or control them
•	They operated in shadows—urban legends, conspiracy theories, "unexplained phenomena"
•	The two fighters? They were among the absolute strongest Resolve users on the planet
________________________________________
THE COLLISION - TWO MONTHS AGO
What Actually Happened:
The fight between the two titans wasn't just physical—it was a clash of pure, concentrated Resolve.
When their ultimate attacks collided, something unprecedented occurred:
"The Rupture" - Their Resolve energies didn't cancel out... they shattered and scattered.
Like a mirror exploding, fragments of their impossibly concentrated willpower blasted outward in a shockwave, infecting everyone in the blast zone.
The Effect:
Instead of people naturally awakening their own Resolve over years, thousands of people had foreign Resolve fragments forcibly jammed into their souls.
The Result:
•	Anyone with existing internal conflict had that conflict weaponized
•	Their contradictions, fears, suppressed desires became parasitic Resolve patterns
•	Most people's psyches couldn't handle it—they went mad, died, or barely changed
•	Some, like your MC, had their internal war become a literal split personality with its own Resolve
This is why it's chaos:
•	These people didn't earn their power through conviction—they were infected by someone else's
•	Their abilities are unstable, conditional, often self-destructive
•	They're using power their souls weren't built to handle
________________________________________
THE NEW WORLD - TWO MONTHS POST-COLLISION
Complete Pandemonium:
Society is Barely Holding Together:
•	Martial Law in The Scar district and surrounding areas
•	Thousands dead, infrastructure destroyed, reality itself is glitchy in Ground Zero
•	Government scrambling to contain the situation—it's barely been 8 weeks!
•	Mass panic, riots, religious movements claiming it's the apocalypse
•	Economy in freefall in affected regions
The Changed Ones (now called "The Ruptured"):
Not organized categories yet—it's too soon. Just chaos:
•	Most Ruptured are weak/unstable - flickering abilities, mental breaks, dying from the strain
•	Some are terrifyingly strong - usually the ones who were already close to awakening naturally
•	The Pre-Collision Resolve Users (let's call them "Naturals") are watching this with a mix of horror and opportunity
Three Groups Emerge Fast:
1.	The Naturals (Pre-existing Resolve users) 
o	They see the Ruptured as abominations, mistakes, or opportunities
o	Some are hunting Ruptured to steal/absorb their fragments
o	Others are recruiting them
o	A few are trying to "fix" the situation (find a way to extract the foreign Resolve)
o	They're still the apex predators—most Ruptured are babies playing with fire
2.	The Government/Military 
o	Containment Protocol - kill or capture dangerous Ruptured
o	Trying to study the phenomenon, replicate it, weaponize it
o	Recruiting stable Ruptured for a new special forces division
o	Covering up the existence of Pre-Collision Naturals (classified programs)
3.	The Underground (Forming rapidly) 
o	The Pits just started last month—Ruptured fighting for cash and survival
o	Criminal organizations recruiting/exploiting Ruptured
o	Black market for Resolve suppressors, enhancers, experimental treatments
o	"The Climb" - an informal ranking system already emerging (people desperate for structure/meaning)
________________________________________
THE RESOLVE SYSTEM - MECHANICS
For Naturals (Pre-Collision):
✓ Stable, refined abilities based on their core conviction ✓ Full control, trained techniques ✓ Abilities grow with their Resolve strength ✓ Weakness: Losing conviction/purpose weakens them drastically
For Ruptured (Post-Collision):
✗ Unstable, often conditional abilities ✗ Powers based on their internal contradictions/conflicts ✗ Foreign Resolve fragments fighting their natural soul ✗ Can be incredibly strong but unpredictable ✗ Many are dying—their bodies can't handle the strain after weeks/months
Your MC is Unique:
•	His internal conflict was SO perfectly balanced (restraint vs rage, ambition vs fear)
•	The Resolve fragment split cleanly into two distinct patterns
•	Instead of tearing him apart, it created two complete Resolve users in one body
•	Host has defensive/analytical Resolve pattern
•	Other has offensive/instinctive Resolve pattern
•	If they could unify? He'd be Natural-tier, possibly stronger
________________________________________
YOUR MC'S SITUATION - TWO MONTHS IN
Day of The Collision:
•	He was in his apartment, spiraling about his future, arguing with himself
•	The wave hit
•	Blacked out
•	Woke up three days later in a shelter, The Other already there in his head
The Last Two Months:
•	Total chaos—he's been in survival mode
•	The Other has taken control at least a dozen times (Host keeps "failing" the pact)
•	He's discovered he has powers but has NO idea how to use them properly
•	Been hiding in The Scar district, doing odd jobs, trying to stay under the radar
•	The Other wants to enter The Pits immediately—"We're wasting time! Everyone's scrambling for power RIGHT NOW!"
Current Crisis Point:
•	Money's running out
•	Strange people are sniffing around—Naturals can sense something unusual about him
•	A government sweep is coming to their district next week
•	The Pits are offering huge cash prizes for new fighters (everyone wants fresh blood)
•	The Other makes his ultimatum: "We enter The Pits this weekend, or I'm taking over permanently. Your choice, coward."
________________________________________
STORY THEMES WITH THIS SETUP:
•	Conviction vs Contradiction - Naturals are unified, Ruptured are fractured
•	Earned vs Given - The resentment between those who trained for years vs those "gifted" power
•	Identity in Chaos - Who are you when the world breaks and you break with it?
•	Making It Big in The Apocalypse - When society crumbles, the ambitious rise
________________________________________
