yes it does ... should we include something more resolve energy
HELL YES! Let's make Resolve DEEPER and more versatile. Here's the expanded system:
________________________________________
RESOLVE - THE COMPLETE SYSTEM
Core Concept:
Resolve isn't just "willpower"—it's the materialization of human conviction into reality-altering force. The universe bends, slightly, to those who refuse to bend themselves.
________________________________________
THE THREE PILLARS OF RESOLVE
1. CONVICTION (The Source)
•	Your core drive, obsession, or unshakeable belief
•	Examples: 
o	"I will protect my family no matter what"
o	"I will become the strongest"
o	"I will expose the truth"
o	"I will never submit to anyone"
•	The more specific and intense, the stronger your Resolve
•	Contradiction weakens it - if you doubt your conviction, your power falters
2. MANIFESTATION (The Form)
•	How your Resolve expresses itself in the physical world
•	Divided into Five Types:
A) ENFORCEMENT - Imposing your will directly
•	Enhanced physical abilities, overwhelming presence
•	"My punch WILL land" type energy
•	Berserker styles, unstoppable force
•	Example: The Other's combat style
B) DENIAL - Rejecting reality/attacks through conviction
•	Defensive barriers, negation, immunity
•	"That attack doesn't work on me because I refuse it"
•	Perfect counters, analytical defense
•	Example: Host's defensive abilities
C) PROJECTION - Extending your will outward
•	Energy blasts, constructs, ranged attacks
•	Creating weapons/tools from pure Resolve
•	Territory control, zone dominance
D) DOMINION - Controlling external forces/people
•	Manipulation, compulsion, environmental control
•	"You will do as I say"
•	Mind games, tactical field control
E) TRANSMUTATION - Altering yourself or matter
•	Shapeshifting, body modification, material transformation
•	"I am not what I was"
•	Adaptation, evolution mid-fight
Most people have ONE type. Naturals might develop a secondary over years. Your MC has TWO (split between personalities).
3. INTENSITY (The Fuel)
•	How much Resolve you can channel at once
•	Burns through your conviction like stamina
•	The Cost: 
o	Low Intensity: Sustainable, controlled, weak
o	Mid Intensity: Balanced power and endurance
o	High Intensity: Devastating but draining
o	MAX INTENSITY: "Resolve Burn" - you stake everything on one moment
Resolve Burn:
•	You channel EVERYTHING into a single action
•	Temporarily gain power far beyond your normal limit
•	The Risk: If you fail, your Resolve shatters—you lose your powers, maybe permanently
•	"I stake my entire conviction on this attack landing"
•	This is how weaker fighters can challenge stronger ones
________________________________________
RESOLVE COLORS/AURAS
When Resolve is actively used, it becomes visible:
Natural Resolve Users:
•	Clean, solid colors based on personality/conviction
•	Stable auras, controlled emission
•	Examples: 
o	Gold = Leadership, protection
o	Crimson = Bloodlust, dominance
o	Silver = Precision, perfection
o	Violet = Ambition, hunger for more
Ruptured Resolve:
•	Fractured, flickering, chaotic colors
•	Often multi-colored or shifting (showing internal conflict)
•	Can look "infected" or corrupted
•	Unstable emission—surges and drops
Your MC specifically:
•	Host: Pale blue/white (clarity, analysis, defense) - but it flickers
•	Other: Deep red/black (rage, instinct, offense) - burns intensely
•	When they're close to cooperation: The colors start to MIX into something new (purple/violet = unified ambition)
•	This visual cue shows their relationship status
________________________________________
RESOLVE TECHNIQUES & APPLICATIONS
Basic Applications Everyone Can Learn:
RESOLVE SENSE (Passive)
•	All users can "feel" other people's Resolve
•	Sense their conviction strength, emotional state, killing intent
•	Like a sixth sense for danger/power levels
•	Naturals are expert at this—they can read you like a book
•	Ruptured are often sloppy, their Resolve "leaks" emotions
RESOLVE EMISSION (Active)
•	Releasing your aura to intimidate, communicate, or pressure opponents
•	Can crush weaker-willed people without touching them
•	"This is who I am—can you withstand it?"
•	Creates territory/presence in an area
RESOLVE REINFORCEMENT (Active)
•	Coating yourself/objects with Resolve for enhancement
•	Basics that everyone learns first
•	Punch harder, move faster, break less
•	Efficiency separates amateurs from experts
RESOLVE CONTRACTS (Advanced)
•	Binding your Resolve with conditions for power boosts
•	"If X happens, I get Y power increase"
•	Examples: 
o	"The more damage I take, the stronger I become"
o	"I can only use my power when protecting someone"
o	"My abilities triple at night but I'm powerless during day"
•	Risk: Breaking your own contract shatters your Resolve temporarily
________________________________________
UNIQUE RESOLVE PHENOMENA
RESOLVE RESONANCE
•	When two people with similar convictions fight together
•	Their Resolve amplifies each other
•	Can perform combination techniques
•	This is what Host and Other COULD do but currently can't
RESOLVE CLASH
•	When two powerful convictions directly oppose
•	Creates shockwaves, reality distortions
•	The stronger conviction wins
•	This is what caused The Collision - two titan-level clashes that broke reality
RESOLVE PREDATION
•	Some Naturals have developed techniques to steal/absorb Resolve from others
•	Incredibly taboo and difficult
•	Usually requires killing the target
•	The Ruptured are vulnerable to this—their Resolve is already fragmented
•	Major threat: Naturals hunting Ruptured for power
RESOLVE DEATH
•	When someone's conviction completely shatters
•	They become a "Hollow"—alive but empty, no willpower, no drive
•	Walking vegetables who can't even care about survival
•	Fate worse than death for most
________________________________________
YOUR MC'S RESOLVE BREAKDOWN
HOST:
•	Conviction: "I will prove I matter without becoming a monster"
•	Type: DENIAL (Defensive, analytical)
•	Techniques: 
o	"Overthink Protocol" - Processes multiple combat scenarios, predicts attacks
o	"Rejection Barrier" - Denies attacks through perfect counters/redirection
o	"Consequence Mapping" - Sees the aftermath of actions before committing
•	Color: Flickering pale blue
•	Weakness: Paralysis by analysis, loses power when he doubts himself
THE OTHER:
•	Conviction: "I will seize everything I want, consequences be damned"
•	Type: ENFORCEMENT (Offensive, instinctive)
•	Techniques: 
o	"Zero Hesitation" - Pure offensive output, overwhelming force
o	"Momentum Burn" - Gets stronger the longer the fight continues
o	"Reckless Certainty" - Converts injuries into rage fuel
•	Color: Intense deep red/black
•	Weakness: No strategy, burns through stamina, leaves Host's body damaged
POTENTIAL UNIFIED FORM (Late-game):
•	Conviction: "I will claim my place at the top, as myself, completely"
•	Types: Both DENIAL and ENFORCEMENT simultaneously
•	Color: Royal purple/violet (ambition perfected)
•	Ability: Perfect balance of overwhelming offense with impenetrable defense
•	Name: Could be something like "Unbroken Resolve" or "Paradox King"
________________________________________
RESOLVE IN COMBAT - MIND GAMES
Because Resolve is based on conviction, fights become psychological:
•	Trash talk matters - Shaking someone's confidence weakens their Resolve
•	Showing certainty - Even if you're bluffing, appearing unshaken boosts your power
•	Breaking spirits - Some fighters specialize in psychological warfare
•	Contracts mid-fight - "If I land this hit, my next attack is 10x stronger"
•	Resolve Reads - Sensing when someone's about to Resolve Burn and countering
________________________________________
QUESTIONS THIS RAISES FOR YOUR STORY:
1.	Can Host and Other eventually learn to share Resolve? (Character growth arc)
2.	Are there other "split" Ruptured, or is MC unique? (Plot significance)
3.	What was the conviction of the two original fighters? (Mystery/lore)
4.	Can Ruptured become Naturals if they resolve their conflicts? (Hope/goal)
5.	What happens if someone absorbs MC's Resolve? (Stakes/threat)
________________________________________
Does this make Resolve feel like a complete combat system? Want me to design some example enemy Resolve users, or develop specific techniques for The Pits fights?
