they can eventually as the story progresses but the major starting part of story is involving mc learning and adjusting to his powers and abilities and so is his other self ... mc is unique - only he has a other self which is generally considered bad according to older sayings (this will be covered later part of story)... nah when the resolve becomes 0 , they can gain it back if they dont try get into combat or get into defensive moves to protect their core cause thats where their resolved energy lies
PERFECT! This adds so much more depth. Let me integrate these elements:
________________________________________
RESOLVE CORE SYSTEM (Updated)
THE RESOLVE CORE
Every Resolve user has a "Core"—the central point in their body where their conviction crystallizes into energy.
Core Location:
•	Usually in the chest/heart area (metaphorically and literally where your "drive" lives)
•	Some rare users have it elsewhere (head for intellectual convictions, gut for instinctual ones)
•	Your MC has TWO cores (or one split core)—physical manifestation of his split personality
How It Works:
•	Your Core generates and stores Resolve energy
•	When you use abilities, you're drawing from the Core
•	Hitting 0 Resolve ≠ Permanent Death (unlike what people feared initially)
________________________________________
RESOLVE DEPLETION & RECOVERY
When You Hit Zero:
What Happens:
•	You're completely defenseless—no powers, no enhanced abilities
•	Physically exhausted, vulnerable
•	BUT your conviction itself isn't destroyed (unless you truly give up)
•	Your Core is empty but intact
Recovery Methods:
1. REST & WITHDRAWAL
•	Stop fighting, get to safety
•	Your Core passively regenerates Resolve over time
•	Speed depends on: 
o	How strong your conviction still is
o	Physical rest and mental state
o	Whether you're in a safe environment
•	Could take hours to days depending on depletion severity
2. DEFENSIVE MEDITATION
•	Actively protect your Core while it recovers
•	Don't engage in offense—pure defense/evasion
•	Speeds up recovery if you can maintain safety
•	Risk: If your Core takes a direct hit while depleted, you're in serious trouble
3. CONVICTION REAFFIRMATION
•	Reminding yourself WHY you fight
•	Mental/emotional reset
•	Can jumpstart recovery in critical moments
•	"Remember what you're fighting for"
________________________________________
CORE DAMAGE - THE REAL DANGER
What Actually Destroys You:
CORE SHATTERING:
•	If someone attacks your Core directly when it's depleted (at 0 Resolve)
•	Or if you suffer massive damage while already empty
•	This causes "Resolve Death" (becoming a Hollow)
•	Your conviction is physically broken
Signs of Core Damage:
•	Coughing up blood with Resolve energy mixed in (colored by your aura)
•	Flickering/cracking aura even when trying to emit
•	Sudden drops in power mid-fight
•	Difficulty maintaining conviction mentally
Protecting Your Core:
•	Most fighters instinctively guard their chest
•	Why defensive abilities are crucial even for offensive fighters
•	Advanced technique: "Core Shroud"—wrapping your Core in a constant thin layer of Resolve (drains energy but protects it)
________________________________________
YOUR MC'S UNIQUE CORE SITUATION
The Split Core:
Instead of one unified Core, MC has:
HOST'S CORE (Left side of chest)
•	Generates defensive/analytical Resolve (pale blue)
•	Stable but limited output
•	Focuses on efficiency and preservation
OTHER'S CORE (Right side of chest)
•	Generates offensive/instinctive Resolve (deep red)
•	Powerful but burns fast
•	Focuses on maximum output
The Space Between:
•	There's a gap/fracture between the two Cores
•	This is the physical manifestation of their split
•	Energy leaks through the crack (inefficiency)
•	If they ever unify: The cores would merge into one central Core with combined power
Visual in Combat:
•	When Host is in control: Left side glows, right side dim
•	When Other is in control: Right side blazing, left side faint
•	When they're cooperating: BOTH sides light up and energy arcs between them
________________________________________
COMBAT IMPLICATIONS - EARLY STORY
MC's Learning Curve:
Week 1-2 Post-Collision:
•	Didn't even know he HAD a Core
•	Powers activating randomly
•	The Other taking over when Host's Resolve depletes
•	No control, pure chaos
Months 1-2 (Current Point):
•	Starting to understand basics
•	Can feel when Resolve is low
•	Learning to NOT fight when depleted
•	The Other is frustrated: "You keep running! We could be WINNING!"
•	Host is terrified of Core damage: "We could DIE if we're not careful!"
Early Pits Arc:
•	First real combat training ground
•	Learning to manage Resolve economy
•	Key lesson: Sometimes surviving IS winning
•	Both personalities learning their limits
The Pact Evolution:
Initial Pact (Month 1):
•	Host keeps body unless he "fails to make a point"
•	Very vague, causes constant switches
•	Host keeps losing control at bad times
Refined Pact (Month 2 - Current):
•	Host controls the body in daily life and strategic situations
•	Other gets control in direct combat OR when Host's Resolve hits critical levels (20% or below)
•	Emergency Clause: If Core is in danger, whoever can protect it better takes over instantly
•	Negotiation Possible: They can agree to switch early if situation demands it
Future Development:
•	Learning to hot-swap mid-combat (Host analyzes, Other executes)
•	Sharing Resolve between cores (Host supports, Other attacks)
•	Eventually: Fighting simultaneously with merged consciousness
________________________________________
THE "OTHER SELF" STIGMA (Setup for later story)
Old Sayings/Folklore:
"A man with two hearts has none" "The divided soul serves no master" "When the self argues, demons listen"
What This Hints At:
•	Ancient texts/prophecies about split-core users
•	Historical cases that ended badly (betrayal, madness, destruction)
•	Religious/spiritual implications—"You cannot serve two convictions"
•	Why this matters later: MC will discover there's a REASON split-cores are feared
Naturals' Perspective:
•	Some Naturals can SENSE MC's dual cores
•	They see him as an abomination, a mistake, or a threat
•	"Your existence defies the fundamental rule of Resolve—singular conviction"
•	Others see him as a curiosity or potential weapon
________________________________________
TRAINING & GROWTH SYSTEM
What MC Needs to Learn (Early Game):
CORE BASICS:
1.	Resolve Sense - Feeling his own and others' energy levels
2.	Core Protection - Instinctive guarding, defensive posture
3.	Emission Control - Not leaking Resolve everywhere (currently very sloppy)
4.	Recovery Discipline - Knowing when to retreat and regenerate
COMBAT FUNDAMENTALS: 5. Resolve Reinforcement - Basic enhancement 6. Type Efficiency - Using Denial and Enforcement properly 7. Reading Opponents - Sensing their Resolve to gauge strength 8. Core Strike Recognition - Identifying when someone's aiming for his Core
DUAL-CORE SPECIFIC: 9. Switch Timing - When to let Other take over vs fighting through 10. Resolve Sharing - Eventually learning to pool their energy 11. Simultaneous Control - The endgame ability
How The Pits Will Teach Him:
•	Every fight is a lesson in Resolve management
•	Opponents with different styles force adaptation
•	Losing teaches more than winning early on
•	Other fighters will TARGET his Core once they figure out he's vulnerable
•	He'll face other Ruptured learning their powers too
•	Eventually face Naturals who will HUMILIATE him (showing how far he has to go)
________________________________________
CORE DAMAGE SCENARIOS (Story Beats)
Early Arc - The First Scare:
•	MC gets cocky/desperate, burns through all Resolve
•	Opponent goes for Core strike while he's at 0
•	Emergency switch: Other takes over instantly, pure survival mode
•	Barely escapes, learns to NEVER let Core hit 0 in combat again
Mid Arc - Core Revelation:
•	Someone with Resolve Sense sees his dual cores
•	"What the fuck ARE you?"
•	Word spreads—he becomes known in The Pits as "Two-Heart" or similar
•	Attracts wrong kind of attention (Naturals interested in studying/hunting him)
Late Arc - Unity Tease:
•	Moment of perfect cooperation between Host and Other
•	Both Cores flare simultaneously
•	Brief glimpse of their true potential
•	Sets up the endgame goal: complete fusion
________________________________________
Does this Core system feel solid? Want me to sketch out some early Pits opponents who would teach MC different lessons, or develop the "Other Self" lore for the later story reveals?
