STORY STRUCTURE - FULL BREAKDOWN
________________________________________
OPENING - "THE RUPTURE" (Prologue/Chapter 1)
The Collision Flashback (2 months ago):
Opening Scene:
•	Massive aerial battle above the city
•	Two titans clashing—reality warping around them
•	Citizens fleeing, military helpless
•	The Final Clash: Both unleash everything
•	Screen goes WHITE
Cut to MC's apartment:
•	18-year-old MC alone, spiraling
•	Internal monologue: bills piling up, no direction, comparing himself to everyone else
•	"What's the point of any of this? Why do I even exist?"
•	Arguing with himself about taking risks vs playing it safe
•	The wave hits
•	Everything distorts
•	His internal argument becomes PHYSICAL—he sees a shadowy version of himself
•	"Finally... I can make you listen."
•	Blackout
Wake up:
•	Three days later
•	Government shelter
•	Chaos everywhere—people screaming, powers manifesting, deaths
•	MC stumbles outside into a broken city
•	The Other's voice, clear as day: "About time. We've got work to do."
