ACT 2: THE CLIMB (Chapters 16-40)
ARC 2: "ENTER THE PITS" (First Taste of Ambition)
Timeline: Month 2 (Current story start point could be here for faster pacing)
Story Beats:
Chapters 16-20: The Ultimatum
•	Bills due, money gone, living in a shithole
•	The Other's ultimatum: "We enter The Pits or I'm taking over permanently."
•	MC researches The Pits—illegal fighting ring for Ruptured
•	Cash prizes, rankings, reputation
•	"This is insane. We'll die."
•	"Or we'll finally LIVE. Your choice."
•	MC agrees—refined Pact 2.0 established
•	Registers for The Pits under a nickname (you choose—maybe "Paradox" or "Split")
Chapters 21-25: First Blood
•	FIGHT 1: Low-tier Ruptured, basic Enforcement type
•	MC tries to fight, starts losing
•	Resolve drops to 30%—panic
•	Switch happens mid-fight
•	Other takes over, wins brutally
•	Crowd goes WILD
•	Prize money: enough for next month's rent
•	They taste victory
Chapters 26-30: Building Reputation
•	Series of fights, alternating control
•	MC learning when to fight, when to switch
•	FIGHT 2: Tactical opponent (Dominion type—tries to manipulate MC)
•	Host has to stay in control for this one (mental warfare)
•	Barely wins by outlasting opponent
•	Other: "See? You CAN do it when you have to."
FIGHT 3: Berserker type (pure Enforcement)
•	Other's turn
•	Complete domination
•	Crowd starts recognizing "the fighter who changes styles mid-match"
•	Nickname spreads: "Two-Face" or "Jekyll" (you decide)
Chapters 31-35: The Complication
•	MC catches the eye of PIT BOSS—a mid-tier Natural
•	"You're interesting, kid. I want to see how far you can go."
•	Offers sponsorship (better fights, more money, protection)
•	Cost: Fight in higher-tier matches (way more dangerous)
•	MC hesitates
•	Other: "This is what we WANTED. Say yes."
•	They accept
Chapters 36-40: The Wall
•	FIGHT 4: First high-tier opponent
•	Another Ruptured with refined abilities
•	BOTH Host and Other struggle
•	They're outmatched
•	Forced cooperation: Mid-fight switch becomes a strategy
•	Host analyzes, Other executes
•	They WIN, barely
•	Realize: "We're stronger together... but we still don't trust each other."
•	Arc climax: Someone in the crowd RECOGNIZES his dual Cores
•	Word starts spreading
Arc 2 Theme: "Strength isn't enough—you need purpose."
