ARC 3: "HUNTED" (The Natural Threat)
Timeline: Month 3
Story Beats:
Chapters 41-45: The Attention
•	Rumors spread about "the Ruptured with two Cores"
•	Naturals start attending The Pits to see MC
•	ANTAGONIST INTRODUCTION: A Natural named [You choose name]
•	Mid-30s, Resolve Predator (can steal/absorb others' Resolve)
•	Obsessed with the idea of collecting MC's dual cores
•	"Imagine the power of two convictions in one body... if I take BOTH."
Chapters 46-50: The Hunt Begins
•	MC's apartment is attacked
•	Barely escapes with Other's help
•	Goes into hiding
•	Pit Boss offers protection... for a price
•	"Fight in my championship bracket. Win, and I'll keep you safe."
•	The bracket: 8 fighters, single elimination, winner gets massive prize + reputation
Chapters 51-60: Tournament Arc
•	FIGHT 5: Projection-type Ruptured (ranged combat specialist)
•	Forces MC to learn defensive mobility
•	Host takes lead, learns to redirect attacks
•	Victory
FIGHT 6: Transmutation-type (shapeshifter, adaptive)
•	Other's turn
•	Opponent keeps evolving to counter attacks
•	Other has to get CREATIVE, not just brutal
•	Hard-fought victory
FIGHT 7 (Semi-Final): Another dual-personality Ruptured
•	MIRROR MATCH
•	But THIS fighter has their personalities cooperating from the start
•	MC and Other get WRECKED initially
•	Mid-fight crisis: "We have to work together. Actually together."
•	First true Resolve Resonance moment
•	Both cores flare, energy bridges between them
•	They win, but it's brief—they snap back to conflict after
FIGHT 8 (Final): A Natural enters the ring
•	Not the Predator, but another Natural "testing" the Ruptured
•	MC gets HUMILIATED
•	Realize how far they have to go
•	Natural toys with them, wins easily
•	"You're strong for a Ruptured. But you'll never be one of us."
•	Arc climax: The Predator attacks immediately after (MC is depleted)
•	Pit Boss intervenes, fight breaks out
•	MC barely escapes in the chaos
•	The Predator's promise: "I'll find you. And I'll take everything you are."
Arc 3 Theme: "There's always a bigger monster."
