ACT 3: EVOLUTION (Chapters 61-90)
ARC 4: "THE UNDERGROUND WAR"
Timeline: Months 4-5
Story Beats:
Chapters 61-70: Going Deeper
•	MC goes underground (literally—deeper into The Scar)
•	Discovers hidden community of Ruptured
•	MEET ALLIES: 
o	Other Ruptured learning their powers
o	Someone with knowledge about Pre-Collision Resolve history
o	Potential love interest (another Ruptured with her own struggles)
•	Learn about The Naturals' Secret: They're organizing, planning something
•	Rumors of Resolve Predation rings—Naturals farming Ruptured for power
Chapters 71-80: Training Arc
•	MC NEEDS to get stronger
•	Learns advanced techniques: 
o	Core Shroud (protecting his Cores)
o	Resolve Contracts (self-imposed limitations for power boosts)
o	Dual-core synchronization exercises
•	Character development: Host and Other start having actual CONVERSATIONS
•	"Why do YOU want to make it big?"
•	"Same reason as you... I want to matter. I want to prove we're not a mistake."
•	"...Yeah. Me too."
Chapters 81-90: The Raid
•	Naturals raid the underground community
•	MAJOR BATTLE
•	MC has to protect people (first time fighting for something beyond himself)
•	The Predator returns
•	Final confrontation of this arc
•	MC and Other fight in SYNC for the first time (not perfect, but close)
•	They drive the Predator off, but don't defeat him
•	Cost: The community is scattered, some die, MC's Core takes damage
•	Needs serious recovery time
Arc 4 Theme: "What are you fighting FOR?"
________________________________________
ARC 5: "THE TRUTH" (Mystery/Lore)
Timeline: Month 6
Story Beats:
Chapters 91-100: The Investigation
•	MC discovers ancient texts about "The Divided"
•	Historical cases of split-core users
•	The Pattern: They all went mad, betrayed everyone, or were killed
•	"A soul at war with itself will destroy everything it touches"
•	The Fear: Is MC doomed to the same fate?
Chapters 101-110: The Original Fighters
•	Research into the two titans who caused The Collision
•	REVELATION: One of them WAS a split-core user who achieved unification
•	The other was hunting them for it
•	The Collision wasn't a random fight—it was an assassination attempt
•	The split-core user CHOSE to fracture themselves and scatter the energy
•	"If I can't exist whole, then everyone will carry a piece of me..."
•	Implication: MC is carrying a FRAGMENT of the original's Resolve
•	That's why his split is so perfect, so powerful
Chapters 111-120: The Conspiracy
•	Naturals have been hunting split-cores specifically
•	They know about the original fighter
•	They're trying to RECONSTITUTE the original by collecting all the split-core Ruptured
•	MC is the ONLY complete dual-core (others are partial or broken)
•	He's the key to their plan
•	"We need to disappear. NOW."
•	"No. We need to stop them."
•	First time Host and Other agree on something risky
Arc 5 Theme: "Know what you are before you become it."
