THE PITS OPPONENTS ROSTER
Here's a breakdown of fighters MC faces, their purposes narratively:
TIER 1: LEARNING CURVE (Arc 2, Early Fights)
1. "BRAWLER" - First Opponent
•	Type: Enforcement (basic punches, no technique)
•	Conviction: "I'll beat anyone in front of me"
•	Lesson: Raw power isn't enough—Host learns this when he loses, Other learns when he wins easily
•	Outcome: Other's victory, quick
2. "PUPPETEER" - Mind Games
•	Type: Dominion (tries to manipulate/compel opponents)
•	Conviction: "Everyone has strings I can pull"
•	Lesson: Mental fortitude matters—Host MUST stay in control or lose his mind
•	Outcome: Host's hard-fought victory, learns Resolve isn't just physical
3. "JUGGERNAUT" - Pure Destruction
•	Type: Enforcement (unstoppable charging attacks, high durability)
•	Conviction: "Nothing can stop me"
•	Lesson: Sometimes overwhelming force is the answer—Other's specialty
•	Outcome: Other's dominant victory, crowd favorite moment
________________________________________
TIER 2: GETTING SERIOUS (Arc 2, Mid-Tier)
4. "SHARPSHOOTER" - Range Specialist
•	Type: Projection (energy blasts, constructs, zoning)
•	Conviction: "Distance is safety, precision is victory"
•	Lesson: Host learns mobility, evasion, closing gaps
•	Outcome: Host's victory after adapting tactics mid-fight
5. "MIMIC" - Adaptive Fighter
•	Type: Transmutation (copies opponent's moves, evolves during fight)
•	Conviction: "I become whatever beats you"
•	Lesson: Other can't just brute force—needs creativity
•	Outcome: Other's victory through unpredictable aggression
6. "MIRROR" - Another Dual-Core (Semi-final)
•	Type: BOTH Denial + Enforcement (like MC)
•	Conviction: "We are complete together" (personalities cooperate)
•	Lesson: CRITICAL FIGHT—shows MC what he COULD be
•	Outcome: MC's desperate victory through first Resonance moment, but Mirror had them beat until then
________________________________________
TIER 3: THE WALL (Arc 2 Final, Arc 3)
7. "THE NATURAL" - Reality Check
•	Type: Refined Dominion (territory control, psychological warfare)
•	Conviction: "Ruptured are temporary, I am eternal"
•	Lesson: HUMBLING DEFEAT—shows the gap between Ruptured and Naturals
•	Outcome: Complete loss, MC can't even touch him
________________________________________
TIER 4: RIVALS & THREATS (Arc 3-4)
8. "THE PREDATOR" - Main Antagonist (Multiple Encounters)
•	Type: Unique—Resolve Predation (steals/absorbs others' Cores)
•	Conviction: "I will become perfect by consuming all of you"
•	Encounters: 
o	First: MC barely escapes (end of Arc 3)
o	Second: Fight to a draw (mid Arc 4)
o	Final: MC (unified) defeats him (Arc 6 climax)
•	Lesson: MC's ultimate test—can he protect his conviction against someone who wants to EAT it?
9. "APEX" - Unification Goal (Sparring partner/rival)
•	Type: All five types mastered (Natural who achieved peak perfection)
•	Conviction: "I am the pinnacle of what Resolve can be"
•	Lesson: This is the level MC aspires to—someone who unified their entire being
•	Outcome: Multiple fights throughout story, MC slowly closes the gap
________________________________________
SUPPORTING CAST FIGHTERS (Side characters)
"BERSERKER" - Ruptured who lost control, pure rage manifestation (tragedy case)
"TACTICIAN" - Weak Resolve but incredible strategy (Host respects him)
"GAMBLER" - Uses Resolve Contracts exclusively, all-or-nothing fighter (teaches MC about Contracts)
"SAINT" - Healer-type Resolve user (shows not all power is for fighting)
"GHOST" - Stealth/assassination Resolve (teaches MC about Resolve Sense and reading hidden threats)
________________________________________
KEY STORY THEMES THROUGHOUT:
1.	Identity: Who are you when you're at war with yourself?
2.	Conviction vs Doubt: Power comes from certainty, but is certainty always right?
3.	Earned vs Given: Ruptured vs Naturals—who deserves power?
4.	Unity: Two halves becoming whole
5.	Purpose: What does "making it big" actually mean?
