THE OTHER - COMMUNICATION STYLE
Full sentences, regular conversation, like talking to another person in your head.
No caveman speak, no dramatic one-worders unless it's situationally appropriate (like anyone would shout "DUCK!" in the moment).
________________________________________
UPDATED DYNAMICS:
Daily Life Examples:
Morning routine:
MC brushing teeth.

Other: "We should start running in the mornings. Build up stamina."

MC: (internally) It's 6 AM and I barely slept because YOU kept me up.

Other: "I kept YOU up? You're the one who was overthinking that mission debrief for three hours."

MC: (internally) Because YOU almost got us killed showing off!

Other: "We won, didn't we? That's what matters."
________________________________________
At the Resolver cafeteria:
MC eating lunch with his squad.

Tactical Girl: "So what'd you think of today's simulation?"

MC: "It was—"

Other: "Tell her we could've done better if the team actually listened to our calls."

MC: (internally) Don't be an asshole.

Other: "I'm not being an asshole, I'm being honest. We spotted the flanking route and nobody took it."

MC: "—challenging. I think we could improve our communication."

Other: "That's what I just said."

MC: (internally) You said it like a dick.
________________________________________
During a mission briefing:
Captain explaining the operation.

Captain: "—so we'll breach from the north entrance—"

Other: "That's stupid. They'll have that covered. The east side has weaker structural integrity, we could force entry there."

MC: (internally) We're not second-guessing the Captain in front of everyone.

Other: "I'm not saying do it NOW. I'm saying think about it. When this plan goes sideways, remember I called it."

MC: (internally) You don't KNOW it'll go sideways.

Other: "Twenty bucks says it does."

MC: (internally) We share a bank account, idiot.

Other: "...Shut up."
________________________________________
Combat Examples:
Mid-fight coordination:
MC dodging attacks, analyzing patterns.

MC: (internally) He's got a three-hit combo, always ends with an overhead—

Other: "Yeah, I see it. After the overhead, he drops his guard for half a second. That's our window."

MC: (internally) I need another rotation to confirm—

Other: "We don't HAVE another rotation! His Resolve is building. If he gets that next attack off, we're done."

MC: (internally) Fine. Next overhead, you take it.

Other: "Finally. Get ready to switch."

The overhead comes. MC feels the Resolve shift.

Other takes control mid-dodge, inside the guard, devastating counter.

Other: "Told you."
________________________________________
Strategy discussion during a fight:
MC behind cover, opponent is ranged specialist.

Other: "Okay, so charging directly isn't working."

MC: (internally) YOU think?

Other: "Don't start. I had to try. Now we know he's got about fifteen meters of effective range. Beyond that, his constructs lose cohesion."

MC: (internally) So we need to create distance and force him to chase.

Other: "Or we close the gap so fast he can't set up. I can do that."

MC: (internally) Your Resolve is at forty percent. You close that gap and you'll hit zero before you reach him.

Other: "Not if you give me support. You throw up a Rejection Barrier while I charge. Split his focus."

MC: (internally) ...That could work.

Other: "Of course it'll work. Let me drive."

MC: (internally) We do this TOGETHER. I'll maintain the barrier, you handle the approach.

Other: "Fine. On three?"

MC: (internally) On three.

Both: "One... two... THREE!"
________________________________________
Character Development Conversations:
Late night, MC staring at the ceiling:
MC: (internally) You ever wonder what we'd be like if The Collision never happened?

Other: "Probably still in that shitty apartment, scrolling job postings we're too scared to apply for."

MC: (internally) ...Yeah. Probably.

Other: "Is that really what you want? Go back to that?"

MC: (internally) I don't know. At least then I wasn't responsible for whether people live or die.

Other: "You were dying slowly. This? This is actually LIVING. We matter now."

MC: (internally) We matter because we can hurt people.

Other: "We matter because we can PROTECT people. You always focus on the wrong part."

MC: (internally) How are you the optimistic one? You're literally my rage and recklessness personified.

Other: "Because I'm not afraid of what we are. You are. That's the difference."

Silence.

MC: (internally) ...I'm working on it.

Other: "I know. That's why we're still here."
________________________________________
After a difficult mission:
MC in medical, getting patched up from injuries Other sustained.

MC: (internally) You didn't have to go that hard. We could've retreated.

Other: "And let that guy escape? He would've hurt more people."

MC: (internally) And now OUR body is fucked up for the next week.

Other: "It'll heal. It always does. Besides, you would've made the same call."

MC: (internally) ...Maybe.

Other: "Not maybe. Definitely. You just wouldn't have executed it as well."

MC: (internally) You're so full of yourself.

Other: "One of us has to be confident. You're too busy second-guessing everything."

MC: (internally) That's called being careful.

Other: "That's called being scared. There's a difference."

MC: (internally) And there's a difference between confident and reckless.

Other: "Yeah. Results. I get them."

MC: (internally) We BOTH get them. When we work together.

Other: "...Yeah. When we work together."
