STORY LAYOUT - REVISED WITH CHARACTER DEPTH
________________________________________
PREMISE
21-year-old MC gets caught in The Collision (2 months ago) - a clash between two Grade-S Resolve users that creates the Ruptured. His internal conflict splits him into two personalities with separate Resolve cores. Both want to prove they matter, escape his dead-end life, and fill the void left by his broken family.
________________________________________
MC'S BACKGROUND & CRISIS
Pre-Collision Life (Age 18-21):
•	Dropped out of college after 1.5 years (couldn't afford it, lost motivation)
•	Worked dead-end jobs: retail, delivery driver, warehouse
•	Watched former classmates succeed on social media while he stagnated
•	The rot: Wake up, work, scroll phone, sleep, repeat
•	No close friends (childhood loneliness carried forward)
•	Quarter-life crisis hitting hard: "Is this it? Is this all I am?"
Family Situation:
Mother (Age 45):
•	Single mom, struggled financially his whole childhood
•	Made the choice 10 years ago (MC was 11): Gave up MC's younger sister for adoption to a wealthy family
•	"We can't afford two kids. She'll have a better life."
•	MC never forgave her, saw it as abandonment for money
•	Last contact: 1 year ago, huge fight 
o	Mom: "I did what I had to!"
o	MC: "You sold her! For what? We're STILL broke!"
o	Haven't spoken since
Sister (Age 19, two years younger):
•	Name: [You choose - maybe something like Rika, Mira, Yuki]
•	Adopted by wealthy Resolver family (they were Naturals even before Collision)
•	MC doesn't know she became a Resolver
•	She remembers him - has been searching since The Collision
•	Resurfaces in Arc 4 as a high-ranking, borderline psychotic Resolver
•	"Big brother... I finally found you."
The Void:
•	MC grew up lonely - mom working multiple jobs, no dad, lost his sister
•	Never learned to make real connections
•	Keeps people at arm's length
•	The Other formed partially from this loneliness: "At least I'm never alone now... even if it's just me."
