•	Organized, competitive even about chores
•	Creates cleaning schedule (MC and Kaito ignore it)
•	Studies Resolve theory constantly
•	Softens over time, opens up about her own family pressure
Domestic Scenes:
•	Grocery shopping together (Other commenting on everything)
•	Movie nights (arguing over what to watch)
•	Cooking dinner (team effort, chaos)
•	Late-night talks when someone can't sleep
•	MC learning what "home" feels like
KEY MOMENT (Chapter 45):
MC sitting on the couch at 2 AM, can't sleep.

Sara comes out, sees him.

Sara: "Nightmare?"

MC: "...Something like that."

She sits down, doesn't push.

Sara: "You know... I used to think you were just antisocial. But you're not. You're just... scared."

MC: "Of what?"

Sara: "That if you let people in, they'll leave. Like your sister did."

MC freezes.

Sara: "Kaito told me. Hope that's okay."

MC: "...It wasn't her choice."

Sara: "I know. But it still hurt."

Silence.

Sara: "We're not going anywhere, you know. You're stuck with us."

MC: (small smile) "...Yeah. Okay."

Other: "She's right. These idiots aren't leaving."

MC: (internally) Shut up, I'm having a moment.

Other: "I'm having it too, dumbass. It's OUR moment."
