ACT 3: INTERNATIONAL & SISTER ARC (Chapters 61-120)
ARC 4: International Crisis (Chapters 61-90)
Chapters 61-70: The Summit
•	International mission, MC + Division 7 deployed
•	Enter: THE SISTER
SISTER CHARACTER (Age 19):
•	Name: REINA (or your choice)
•	High-ranking Resolver from another division
•	Grade A Resolve user - prodigy level
•	Transmutation/Enforcement hybrid
•	Personality: Cold, efficient, borderline psychotic in combat
•	Adopted family raised her as a weapon
•	"Emotions are weaknesses. I excised mine years ago."
•	But: Obsessed with finding MC since Collision
First Meeting (Chapter 68):
International briefing room. MC sees her across the room.

MC: "...Reina?"

She turns. Face blank. Then—

Reina: "Nii-san." (Big brother)

MC's blood runs cold.

Other: "Oh fuck. That's HER?"

Reina approaches, smiling, but it's WRONG.

Reina: "Ten years. I've been looking for you for ten years."

MC: "Reina, what happened to you—"

Reina: "I became strong. Like you. We're the same now."

MC: "No. We're not—"

Reina: "We're both broken. We're both weapons. Finally, we can be a family again."

Sara (stepping between them): "He's got a family."

Reina's smile drops. Resolve flares.

Reina: "You're not his blood."

Captain Takeshi intervenes before it escalates.
Chapters 71-80: Sister Arc
•	Reina assigned to joint mission with Division 7
•	She's ruthlessly effective but unstable
•	Obsessed with MC - wants to "reclaim" him
•	Sees his friends as "parasites stealing her brother"
•	MC torn between guilt (she suffered while adopted) and horror (what she's become)
•	Climax: Reina goes rogue during mission 
o	Nearly kills civilians to complete objective
o	MC has to fight her
o	"I won't let you become a monster!"
o	"I'm YOUR monster, nii-san. I became this FOR YOU."
•	MC defeats her (barely)
•	She's detained, swears she'll escape
•	Arc ends with MC crying for the first time in years
•	"I lost her twice. Once to money, once to violence."
Chapters 81-90: Recovery
•	MC processing trauma with squad/Division
•	Kaito: "She's alive. That's something."
•	Sara: "You can't save someone who doesn't want saving."
•	Other: "We tried. That's all we could do."
•	Character growth: MC accepts he can't fix everything
•	Continues international mission
