________________________________________
WHY YUKI & HER DEATH?
WHO IS YUKI:
Character Profile:
•	Age 20, Denial-type Ruptured
•	Quiet, observant, keeps to herself
•	Dark past hinted at but never fully revealed
•	MC sees himself in her (both isolated, both hiding pain)
•	They have a few bonding moments during training
•	"We're both broken. Maybe that's okay."
•	She's competent but not the strongest
•	Has a habit of overextending to protect teammates
________________________________________
WHY SHE DIES:
1. ESTABLISHES STAKES EARLY
•	Shows that death is real and permanent
•	Not every character has plot armor
•	Resolvers is DANGEROUS work
•	Sets tone: this isn't a safe story
2. EMOTIONAL IMPACT ON MC
•	First real loss since he started connecting with people
•	Triggers guilt: "I could've saved her if I'd acted faster"
•	The Other takes over to end the threat (shows protective side)
•	Forces MC to confront: "Is this worth it? Am I strong enough?"
•	Character development catalyst
3. BONDS THE SURVIVING SQUAD
•	Kaito, Sara, Daichi, and MC grow closer through shared grief
•	"We can't let her death be for nothing."
•	Creates found family dynamic faster
•	Shows vulnerability between teammates
4. THEMATIC RESONANCE
•	MC's arc is about connection vs isolation
•	Yuki's death shows: Connection means risking loss
•	But MC chooses to keep connecting anyway
•	"It still matters. She still mattered."
5. EFFICIENT STORYTELLING
•	Reduces character count (streamlining)
•	Creates emotional weight without dragging it out
•	One death in training > multiple vague casualties
•	Readers/viewers remember HER specifically
6. FORESHADOWS LATER LOSSES
•	Prepares audience for Jiro's death later
•	Shows MC can survive loss and keep going
•	But each death still HURTS
________________________________________
THE DEATH SCENE (Quick outline):
Setting: Final training exam, live combat scenario
What happens:
•	Squad vs upper-year Resolvers in urban environment
•	Yuki notices enemy flanking Hiro (weak link)
•	She moves to intercept, calls for backup
•	MC sees her, starts moving—hesitates (analyzes best approach)
•	Enemy strikes her Core directly while she's exposed
•	Core shatters, she collapses
•	MC freezes, horror setting in
•	Enemy moves to finish her
•	The Other takes over instantly
•	Brutal, overwhelming force—eliminates threat
•	Too late—Yuki's already gone
•	MC regains control, kneels beside her
•	She's already fading (Hollow state, then death)
•	Last words: "...Did I... protect him?"
•	MC: "Yeah. You did."
•	She smiles, dies
Aftermath:
•	Squad passes exam but traumatized
•	Funeral/memorial
•	MC blames himself
•	The Other: "You hesitated. That's why she's dead."
•	MC: "I know."
•	Sara: "It's not your fault."
•	MC: "Feels like it is."
•	Kaito: "Then get stronger. So it doesn't happen again."
•	This becomes MC's secondary motivation
________________________________________
WHY YUKI SPECIFICALLY (Not Hiro or someone else):
Hiro: Too obvious (weak link dies = predictable) Kaito/Sara/Daichi: Too important to core dynamics, would derail apartment arc Yuki:
•	Close enough to MC for impact
•	Not SO close it destroys him
•	Competent enough that her death feels unfair
•	Mysterious enough that readers wanted to know more (tragic)
•	Perfect balance of emotional weight + story efficiency
________________________________________
READER/VIEWER REACTION GOAL:
"Oh fuck, they actually killed her." "I thought she'd be part of the main team!" "This show doesn't fuck around." "MC better avenge her..." "Okay NOW I'm invested."
