MISSION MONTAGES - UNIQUE CONCEPTS
You said missions should be unique. Here are distinct, memorable ones:
________________________________________
FIELD WORK MISSIONS (Chapters 29-35)
MISSION 1: "THE HOLLOW" (Chapters 29-30)
Concept: Mental breakdown containment
Setup:
•	Ruptured woman (age 28) losing control in residential area
•	Her Resolve is glitching—flaring, sputtering, unstable
•	She's terrified, crying, doesn't want to hurt anyone
•	"Please... I can't stop it... someone help me..."
Unique element:
•	MC has to talk her down, not fight
•	Uses empathy (Host leads)
•	"I know what it's like. Feeling like you're losing yourself."
•	The Other is quiet for once, lets Host handle it
•	She calms down...
Twist:
•	...but her Core is already too damaged
•	She becomes a Hollow while they're talking
•	Empty eyes, collapses
•	MC watches the "person" leave her body
•	Daichi tries to stabilize her—nothing works
Aftermath:
•	She's alive but empty (vegetative state)
•	Family arrives, devastated
•	MC questions: "Did I save her? Or just prolong her suffering?"
•	Takeshi: "You gave her peace at the end. That matters."
Theme: Not every mission has a happy ending
________________________________________
MISSION 2: "THE RING" (Chapters 31-33)
Concept: Underground fighting ring bust
Setup:
•	Illegal Resolve fighting ring in abandoned warehouse district
•	Ruptured forced to fight for rich spectators
•	Division 7 goes undercover
•	MC goes in as a fighter (perfect for The Other)
Unique element:
•	The Other gets to be "legal" for once
•	Host watches from inside while Other fights
•	Other: "This is actually fun when people aren't trying to kill us for real."
•	MC: "They ARE trying to kill us."
•	Other: "Yeah but it's ORGANIZED."
The fights:
•	Other dominates first match (crowd loves him)
•	Second match vs sympathetic Ruptured (forced into this, has family)
•	Host wants to forfeit, Other refuses
•	"If we throw the match, they'll know something's up. Trust me."
•	Other wins but makes it look close, whispers: "Play dead, we're getting you out."
Twist:
•	Ring is funded by Naturals (entertainment + studying Ruptured)
•	Raid goes down, chaos
•	Rich Natural spectators fight back (not civilians, actual combatants)
•	Division 7 vs multiple Naturals
•	First time MC sees the class divide clearly
Aftermath:
•	Ruptured fighters freed
•	But Naturals escape (too connected, political immunity)
•	Kaito: "So they just... get away with it?"
•	Ren: "Welcome to the real world, rookie."
Theme: Justice is complicated, system is broken
________________________________________
MISSION 3: "HOSTAGE HEART" (Chapters 34-35)
Concept: Ruptured terrorists holding civilians
Setup:
•	Group of Ruptured took over a corporate building
•	30 hostages, demands being broadcast
•	"The Naturals hid this power from us! They caused The Collision!"
•	"We're victims of THEIR war!"
Unique element:
•	MC sympathizes with them
•	They're not wrong—Naturals DID hide Resolve
•	But civilians are in danger
•	Moral dilemma: Stop them or join them?
The leader:
•	Ruptured man (age 35), lost his family in The Collision
•	Projection type, has building rigged with Resolve constructs
•	Articulate, passionate, not a monster
•	"We're not villains. We're the oppressed fighting back."
The negotiation:
•	Division 7 tries to negotiate
•	MC volunteers to go in alone (Host leads)
•	Talks with leader
•	"I get it. I'm Ruptured too. I'm angry too."
•	"But killing innocents makes us the monsters they think we are."
•	Leader: "Sometimes you have to be a monster to be heard."
The choice:
•	Negotiation fails, leader starts countdown
•	MC has to fight him
•	The Other takes over mid-fight
•	Brutal, efficient, stops the threat
•	Hostages saved
Aftermath:
•	Leader arrested, broken
•	Thanks MC: "At least... someone understood."
•	MC feels empty (no right answer)
•	Sara: "You saved lives. That's what matters."
•	MC: "Then why do I feel like shit?"
Theme: Right choices can still hurt
________________________________________
WHAT MAKES THESE UNIQUE:
Mission 1: Emotional, no villain, tragedy Mission 2: Undercover, morally gray, class warfare Mission 3: Sympathetic antagonist, no-win scenario
Each teaches MC something different:
1.	Empathy isn't always enough
2.	The system protects the powerful
3.	Being right doesn't mean you feel good
