•	Second: ELIZABETH KURODA (Female, appears 40s, half-Japanese)
•	Various other ancient Naturals
•	Grades: All S-rank
________________________________________
THE ORIGINAL GRADE-S FIGHTERS:
16. "THE FRACTURED ONE" (The split-core fighter who died)
•	Real name unknown
•	Grade: S+ (beyond normal S-rank)
17. "THE ARBITER" (The assassin sent to kill them)
•	Real name unknown
•	Grade: S+
________________________________________
RESOLVE TYPE SYSTEM - DETAILED
THE FIVE CORE TYPES:
________________________________________
1. ENFORCEMENT
One-liner: "Imposing your will directly onto reality through force"
How it works:
•	Enhance physical abilities, overwhelming presence
•	"My attack WILL land because I refuse any other outcome"
•	Raw power, unstoppable momentum
Users:
•	Kaito Nomura: Explosive striking power, gets stronger when protecting others
•	Jiro Saito: Immovable defense, can tank attacks through sheer willpower
•	The Other (Akira's second personality): Pure offensive output, berserker style
•	Reina Kitagawa (hybrid): Combines with Transmutation for devastating effect
NOT the same for each:
•	Kaito = Burst damage
•	Jiro = Durability tank
•	The Other = Sustained aggression
•	Reina = Adaptive brutality
________________________________________
2. DENIAL
One-liner: "Rejecting reality itself through unshakeable conviction"
How it works:
•	Defensive barriers, negation, perfect counters
•	"That attack doesn't exist because I refuse it"
•	Analytical, reactive, protection-focused
Users:
•	Akira Hayashi (Host personality): Predictive analysis, redirects attacks, consequence mapping
•	Yuki Morita: Emotional pain suppression, can negate mental attacks
NOT the same:
•	Akira = Analytical prediction + redirection
•	Yuki = Emotional/mental negation
________________________________________
3. PROJECTION
One-liner: "Extending your will outward as tangible constructs"
How it works:
•	Energy blasts, weapons, constructs made from Resolve
•	Creating matter from conviction
•	Range combat, zone control
Users:
•	Sara Fujimoto: Creates tactical constructs (walls, platforms, ranged attacks), battlefield control
•	Captain Takeshi Kurosawa: Massive-scale constructs, can create entire structures, veteran efficiency
NOT the same:
•	Sara = Tactical variety, adaptable constructs
•	Takeshi = Massive scale, overwhelming power
________________________________________
4. DOMINION
One-liner: "Controlling external forces through absolute authority"
How it works:
•	Manipulation, compulsion, environmental control
•	"You will obey because I command it"
•	Mind games, tactical field dominance
Users:
•	Ren Takahashi: Strategic field control, can sense and manipulate combat flow, detective instincts
•	Ayumi Tanaka: Emotional manipulation for de-escalation, reads and influences feelings
NOT the same:
•	Ren = Combat flow manipulation, strategic
•	Ayumi = Emotional influence, support-focused
________________________________________
5. TRANSMUTATION
One-liner: "Altering the fundamental nature of self or matter"
How it works:
•	Shapeshifting, body modification, material transformation
•	"I am not what I was, I am what I need to be"
•	Adaptation, evolution, versatility
Users:
•	Daichi Yamamoto: Body hardening for defense, can transform limbs into medical tools, healing-focused adaptations
•	Reina Kitagawa (hybrid): Full-body transformation, weaponization, predatory evolution
NOT the same:
•	Daichi = Defensive/healing transformations
•	Reina = Offensive/predatory adaptations
________________________________________
SPECIAL CASES:
HYBRID TYPES (Extremely rare):
•	Can use TWO types (usually family bloodline or split-core cases)
•	Akira Hayashi: Denial (Host) + Enforcement (Other) - split personality unique case
•	Reina Kitagawa: Transmutation + Enforcement - ancestral Kitagawa family bloodline
SENSORY/SUPPORT (Not a "type" but specialized application):
•	Mitsuki Tanaka: Uses Denial-type Resolve to "reject" sensory limitations, creates hyper-awareness field
________________________________________
GRADE HIERARCHY SYSTEM
RESOLVER CLASSIFICATION:
D-RANK: Barely awakened
•	Minimal abilities, mostly civilian-level
•	Can sense Resolve but barely use it
•	Example: Hiro Watanabe (washed out)
C-RANK: Competent field agents
•	Basic combat ability
•	Can handle low-tier threats
•	Most new Ruptured start here
•	Examples: Akira (start), Kaito (start), Daichi (start), Mitsuki (start)
B-RANK: Experienced Resolvers
•	Refined techniques, reliable in most situations
•	Can handle standard missions solo
•	Examples: Sara (start), Ren (start), Akira (mid-story), Kaito (mid-story)
A-RANK: Elite operatives
•	Captain-level, can handle major threats
•	Refined mastery of their type
•	Examples: Captain Takeshi, Jiro, Sara (end), Reina, Akira (end)
S-RANK: Legendary-level threats/protectors
•	Can alter battlefields, defeat entire divisions
•	Few exist globally
•	Examples: The Architects, the original two fighters
S+ RANK (Unofficial):
•	Beyond classification
•	Reality-warping level
•	Only the original "Fractured One" and "Arbiter"
________________________________________
CHARACTER GRADE PROGRESSION:
Character	Start	Mid	End
Akira Hayashi	C	B	A
Kaito Nomura	C	B	B+
Sara Fujimoto	B	B+	A
Daichi Yamamoto	C	C+	B
Yuki Morita	C+	DEAD	-
Mitsuki Tanaka	C+	B-	B-
Ren Takahashi	B+	A-	A
Reina Kitagawa	A	A+	A+
Ayumi Tanaka	B+	B+	A-
