PREDATOR REPLACEMENT OPTIONS
OPTION 1: SHIRO "THE COLLECTOR" ASAKURA
•	Male, mid-30s
•	Former archaeologist obsessed with ancient Resolve artifacts
•	Ability: "Archive" - Can extract and store Resolve patterns from defeated opponents
•	Personality: Intellectual, collector mentality, sees people as "specimens"
•	"Your dual cores would make a perfect addition to my collection."
OPTION 2: "VOID" (Real name: KENTO MORI)
•	Male, late 20s
•	Former Resolver who went rogue
•	Ability: "Consumption" - Absorbs dying Cores, experiences victim's final moments
•	Personality: Nihilistic, addicted to the "high" of absorption, tragic villain
•	"Every Core I take, I feel them die. It's the only time I feel alive."
OPTION 3: HARUKA "THE PARASITE" NISHIMURA
•	Female, early 30s
•	Natural who developed forbidden technique
•	Ability: "Symbiosis" - Temporarily bonds with others' Cores, drains them over time
•	Personality: Charming, manipulative, genuinely believes she's helping
•	"I'm freeing you from the burden of choice. Just let me in."
OPTION 4: "FRAGMENT" (Real name unknown)
•	Ambiguous gender, appears mid-20s
•	Actually a PIECE of the original Fractured One
•	Ability: "Reclamation" - Trying to absorb all split-cores to reconstitute itself
•	Personality: Fragmented (multiple personalities fighting for control), tragic
•	"We... I... we need to be whole again. You understand, don't you?"
MY RECOMMENDATION: OPTION 4 "FRAGMENT"
•	Ties directly into lore (piece of original fighter)
•	Creates mirror to Akira (both are fragmented, both seeking wholeness)
•	Sympathetic villain (wants same thing as MC—unity)
•	Higher stakes (if they succeed, original fighter returns)
•	Can be defeated BEFORE international arc (Act 2 climax)
•	Architects become Act 3 threat
________________________________________
THE ARCHITECTS: GOOD OR BAD?
THEY ARE: MORALLY COMPLEX (Not pure evil)
Their Perspective:
•	"We've protected humanity from Resolve chaos for centuries"
•	"The Fractured One would have exposed everything—caused global war"
•	"The Collision was an accident, but we're trying to fix it"
•	"Ruptured are unstable—many WILL become monsters"
•	"We're maintaining order in a world that would collapse into chaos"
What They Actually Do (Bad):
•	Hunt and experiment on Ruptured
•	Manipulate governments globally
•	Assassinated the Fractured One
•	Fund illegal fighting rings (research + entertainment)
•	Plan to trigger controlled Collision to "reset" (kill all Ruptured)
Nuance:
•	Some members genuinely believe they're protecting humanity
•	Others are just power-hungry
•	Leader Soichiro Yamazaki is True Believer type (dangerous ideologue)
•	They're not wrong that Resolve could destroy society if uncontrolled
•	But their methods are authoritarian and cruel
Resolution:
•	Akira defeats them but doesn't completely dismantle the system
•	Reforms from within (new leadership, Resolver oversight)
•	Some Architects remain (sequel threat)
•	Theme: Systems are complex, revolution isn't always the answer
________________________________________
TRAINING FACILITY NAME OPTIONS:
OPTION 1: THE CRUCIBLE
•	Where Resolvers are "forged" through fire
•	Located in fortified zone outside destroyed districts
•	Harsh name, reflects harsh training
OPTION 2: TENJIN ACADEMY (天神, "Heavenly God")
•	More traditional, prestigious-sounding
•	Named after Shinto god of learning
•	Implies it's the "official" path to becoming a Resolver
OPTION 3: THE FORGE COMPLEX
•	Government facility, militaristic
•	Multiple divisions: training, research, containment
•	Where new Resolvers are "shaped"
OPTION 4: KAZAN INSTITUTE (火山, "Volcano")
•	"Where pressure creates diamonds"
•	Located near actual dormant volcano
•	Metaphor for transformation through extreme conditions
MY RECOMMENDATION: TENJIN ACADEMY
•	Sounds official and prestigious
•	Contrasts with the brutal reality of training
•	Easy to reference ("Tenjin," "the Academy")
•	Has Japanese cultural weight
LOCATION: Outside Tokyo in fortified mountain zone, near where The Collision occurred
________________________________________
YUKI'S DEATH - REVISED (Out of the Blue)
NEW SCENARIO: "Katana Man"-style Unexpected Attack
Setup (Chapter 24-25):
•	Squad has passed mid-terms, celebrating
•	Seems like a victory arc, lowered tension
•	Going out for team dinner in the semi-safe zone near Tenjin Academy
•	Joking around, Yuki is finally opening up
•	First time she's laughed genuinely
•	Akira thinks: "Maybe we'll all make it through this."
The Attack:
•	Random restaurant, casual atmosphere
•	No warning, no buildup
•	Sudden explosion of Resolve energy outside
•	A rogue A-rank Natural crashes through the wall 
o	NOT part of any plan, just went insane
o	Former Architect member who lost family in Collision
o	Blames Ruptured (even though Naturals caused it)
o	"You're all MISTAKES! You shouldn't exist!"
The Fight:
•	Squad scrambles, civilians screaming
•	Natural is WAY above their level (A-rank vs C-rank rookies)
•	Instructors rushing to the scene but minutes away
•	Yuki moves to protect civilians
•	Natural targets her specifically (senses she's Denial type, wants to prove "rejection" is meaningless)
•	Direct Core strike, instant
•	She doesn't even see it coming
The Horror:
•	No dramatic last words
•	No slow death scene
•	Just... gone
•	Core shattered, collapses
•	Akira frozen, can't process
•	The Other takes over instantly 
o	Doesn't win (they're outmatched)
o	But fights savagely, buys time
o	Instructors arrive, subdue the Natural
•	Yuki already dead when Akira regains control
Aftermath:
•	Squad in shock
•	"She was just... laughing. She was finally happy."
•	No heroic sacrifice speech
•	No "tell my family" moment
•	Just random, brutal, UNFAIR
•	Kaito breaks down
•	Sara goes silent for days
•	Daichi questions if he can do this
•	Akira realizes: They can die anytime, anywhere, for no reason
Theme: Death isn't always meaningful. Sometimes it's just cruel.
