ADDRESSING ALL POINTS
________________________________________
1. GRADE SYSTEM REPLACEMENT
You're right—S/A/B/C is overused (Solo Leveling, etc.). Let's create something unique.
________________________________________
NEW RANKING SYSTEM OPTIONS:
OPTION 1: TIER SYSTEM (Roman Numerals)
TIER V (Five) - Awakened (barely functional) TIER IV (Four) - Competent (field ready) TIER III (Three) - Veteran (experienced, reliable) TIER II (Two) - Elite (exceptional, captain-level) TIER I (One) - Apex (legendary, world-shakers)
Why this works:
•	Visual distinctiveness (Roman numerals look different)
•	Descending = "climbing down to perfection" (Tier I is peak)
•	Not used in other major series
________________________________________
OPTION 2: CLASS SYSTEM (Named Tiers)
HOLLOW CLASS - Awakened but weak IRON CLASS - Competent fighters STEEL CLASS - Veteran operatives DIAMOND CLASS - Elite few ZENITH CLASS - Apex beings
Why this works:
•	Material progression metaphor (weak to unbreakable)
•	Zenith ties to "Fractured One" lore
•	Memorable names
________________________________________
OPTION 3: DEPTH SYSTEM (Inversed)
SURFACE - Shallow Resolve, weak DEPTHS - Moderate Resolve ABYSS - Deep Resolve, powerful VOID - Deepest Resolve, rare SINGULARITY - Beyond measurement
Why this works:
•	Thematic: deeper = stronger conviction
•	Ties to internal struggle concept
•	"Void" as a rank makes Kento's codename more meaningful
________________________________________
OPTION 4: RESONANCE LEVELS
DISCORD - Unstable, conflicted Resolve HARMONY - Balanced, functional SYMPHONY - Refined, powerful CRESCENDO - Peak performance OPUS - Masterwork level
Why this works:
•	Musical metaphor fits "two personalities in harmony" theme
•	Unique to your story
•	Elegant terminology
________________________________________
MY RECOMMENDATION: TIER SYSTEM (Option 1)
Why:
•	Clean, professional (Resolvers are government org)
•	Not overused in anime/manga
•	Easy to remember (Tier V → Tier I progression)
•	Works in dialogue: "He's Tier II? We're screwed."
Character Rankings (Revised):
Character	Start	Mid	End
Tetsu Mikage	Tier IV	Tier III	Tier II
Kaito Nomura	Tier IV	Tier III	Tier III
Sara Fujimoto	Tier III	Tier III	Tier II
Daichi Yamamoto	Tier IV	Tier IV	Tier III
Yuki Morita	Tier IV	DEAD	-
Mitsuki Tanaka	Tier IV	Tier III	Tier III
Ren Takahashi	Tier III	Tier II	Tier II
Captain Takeshi	Tier II	Tier II	Tier II
Jiro Saito	Tier II	DEAD	-
Reina Kitagawa	Tier II	Tier I (borderline)	-
Ayumi Tanaka	Tier II (borderline I)	Tier I	-
