THE DISAPPEARANCE (10 Years Ago - Tetsu was 11, Reina was 9):
What Really Happened:
The Setup:
•	Kaito witnessed something he shouldn't have
•	Discovered early Sanctum operations (they existed pre-Collision)
•	Saw them experimenting on potential Resolve users
•	"They're creating weapons out of people..."
•	Planned to expose them
The Choice:
•	Sanctum gave him ultimatum: 
o	"Disappear and your family lives"
o	"Or we kill all three of you"
•	Kaito had 24 hours to decide
The Night He Left:
Kaito watching Tetsu and Reina sleep.

Keiko: "What's wrong?"

Kaito: "I have to leave. Tonight."

Keiko: "What? Why?"

Kaito: "If I stay, they'll die. All of you."

Keiko: "Who—what are you talking about?"

Kaito: (hands her envelope—¥5 million cash) "This is all I have. Take the kids and move. Don't tell anyone where you go."

Keiko: "Kaito, you're scaring me—"

Kaito: "I love you. I love them. That's why I have to go."

Kisses her. Looks at his kids one last time.

Kaito: "Tell them... tell them I'm sorry."

Gone.
Aftermath:
•	Keiko devastated, confused
•	Used the money (lasted ~2 years)
•	Never told kids the truth (didn't understand it herself)
•	Told them: "Your father left us. He didn't care enough to stay."
•	Tetsu grew up believing his father abandoned them for nothing
________________________________________
THE TRUTH REVEALED (Late Act 3 - Ch 95):
How Tetsu Finds Out:
During Sanctum assault, Tetsu discovers archived files:
•	Kaito's name on a list
•	"Witnesses - Terminated or Contained"
•	Status: Contained - Facility 7
Tetsu: "He's... alive?"
Facility 7 Raid:
•	Deep in Sanctum stronghold
•	Tetsu breaks in
•	Finds containment cells
•	There: Kaito Hayashi, age 46, grey hair, thin
•	Tier III → Tier IV (weakened by years of Resolve suppression)
The Reunion:
Kaito looks up. Doesn't recognize him at first.

Tetsu: "...Dad?"

Kaito: (eyes widening) "No. No, you're not— Tetsu?"

Tetsu: "Yeah. It's me."

Kaito stands, chains rattle.

Kaito: "You're so... You're grown. You're—" (seeing the Resolve aura) "You're like me now."

Tetsu: "The Collision. I'm Ruptured."

Kaito: "I tried to stop them. I tried to expose what they were doing. If I'd known they'd cause something like this—"

Tetsu: "You've been here the whole time?"

Kaito: "Ten years. They said if I escaped, they'd kill you. All of you."

Tetsu: (voice breaking) "We thought you left. Mom said you abandoned us."

Kaito: "I left to SAVE you. I left so you could live."

Tetsu: "Reina— they took Reina. Because we were poor. Because you weren't there."

Kaito: (collapsing) "What?"

Tetsu: "The Kitagawa family adopted her. Turned her into a weapon. She's—" (can't finish)

Kaito: "No. No no no— I did this for nothing. I gave up everything and they STILL—"

Tetsu: "We're getting you out. Now."

The Other: (internally) "He stayed for us. He's been in hell for us."

Tetsu: (internally) "I know."
After Rescue:
•	Kaito weak, traumatized, guilt-ridden
•	Meets Keiko again (complicated reunion)
•	Tetsu finally understands sacrifice
•	"He didn't abandon us. He saved us."
•	But Tetsu still doesn't cry in front of him
•	Cries alone later (Ayumi finds him)
Final Scene with Father (Epilogue):
Kaito recovering, visiting the apartment.

Kaito: "You have friends. A home. You built something good."

Tetsu: "Yeah. I guess I did."

Kaito: "I'm proud of you. Both of you." (meaning Host and Other)

Tetsu: "...Thanks, Dad."

Kaito: "Can I ask you something?"

Tetsu: "Sure."

Kaito: "Are you happy?"

Tetsu: (thinking) "...Yeah. I think I am."

Kaito: "Then I didn't fail completely."

They sit in silence. Tetsu almost cries. Doesn't. Smiles instead.

Later, alone in his room, Tetsu finally cries.

The Other: (quietly) "He's a good man."

Tetsu: (internally, wiping tears) "Yeah. He is."
________________________________________
WHY THIS WORKS:
✅ Crucial: His disappearance directly led to family poverty → Reina's adoption ✅ Tragic: He sacrificed everything but couldn't prevent the worst outcome ✅ Thematic: Tetsu learns about real sacrifice (parallels his own journey) ✅ Payoff: Father-son reunion hits HARD emotionally ✅ Tetsu's Character: He still doesn't cry in front of others (cries alone after)
________________________________________
4. TETSU'S CRYING RULE - CHARACTER CONSISTENCY
ESTABLISHED TRAIT:
Tetsu NEVER cries in front of people.
Why:
•	Childhood trauma (feeling abandoned, had to "be strong" for Reina)
•	Fear of vulnerability ("If I break, everything falls apart")
•	The Other mocks him when he's emotional (learned to suppress)
•	Pride/shame mixture
Times He Comes Close But Doesn't:
•	Yuki's death (holds it together)
•	Reina confrontation (swallows it down)
•	Father reunion (fights it back)
•	Jiro's sacrifice (jaw clenched, silent)
Times He Cries ALONE:
•	After Yuki's funeral (in his room, silent tears)
•	After defeating Reina (bathroom, breaks down)
•	After rescuing father (rooftop, finally lets go)
•	Post-unification (one final cry—letting The Other go)
The ONE Exception - Cries in Front of Someone:
Post-father rescue, rooftop, night.

Tetsu sitting alone, finally crying silently.

Ayumi appears (she tracked him).

Tetsu: (immediately wipes face) "I'm fine—"

Ayumi: (sits down, doesn't look at him) "You don't have to be."

Tetsu: "I can't— If I start, I won't stop."

Ayumi: "Then don't stop."

Tetsu: (breaks down completely) "He was there. For ten years. Alone. Because of me. And I HATED him. I hated him for leaving and he was SAVING us—"

Ayumi: (still not looking, lets him cry) "You didn't know."

Tetsu: "Reina— If he'd been there, maybe— maybe she wouldn't—"

Ayumi: "You can't think like that."

Tetsu: (sobbing) "I don't know how to fix any of this."

Ayumi: "You don't have to fix everything. You just have to keep going."

Long silence. Tetsu crying. Ayumi holding his hand.

Ayumi: "I won't tell anyone."

Tetsu: (small laugh through tears) "Thanks."

This is when their relationship becomes REAL.
