1. RANKING SYSTEM - FINAL DECISION
LET'S DO: GRADE SYSTEM (But Make It Unique)
Why Grade works better:
•	Familiar enough to be intuitive
•	Can be stylized uniquely
•	Works well in dialogue
•	But we'll differentiate it visually/conceptually
________________________________________
UNIQUE GRADE SYSTEM: "CORE GRADES"
Instead of S/A/B/C, use:
GRADE ZERO (0) - Apex/Legendary
•	Reserved for world-shakers
•	Single digits globally
•	Examples: Sanctum Lords, Fractured One, Arbiter
GRADE ONE (1) - Elite
•	Captain-level, exceptional
•	~100 worldwide
•	Examples: Ayumi, Reina (borderline), Void (peak)
GRADE TWO (2) - Veteran
•	Experienced, reliable operatives
•	~1,000 worldwide
•	Examples: Takeshi, Ren, Jiro, Sara (end)
GRADE THREE (3) - Competent
•	Field-ready, solid fighters
•	~10,000 worldwide
•	Examples: Tetsu (mid), Kaito, Daichi, Mitsuki
GRADE FOUR (4) - Awakened
•	Basic ability, still learning
•	Most Ruptured start here
•	Examples: Tetsu (start), Yuki, Hiro
GRADE FIVE (5) - Nascent
•	Barely functional, might die from instability
•	Many Ruptured stuck here
•	Rarely make it to active duty
________________________________________
Why this works:
•	Zero is the goal (not S/A/etc.)
•	Lower number = stronger (inverse feels different)
•	"Core Grade" ties to Core system
•	Can say "He's a Two" or "She's Grade One" naturally
•	Visually distinct: [0] [1] [2] [3] [4] [5]
