PART 2: THE OTHER'S SEPARATION - MAJOR PLOT TWIST
THE SETUP:
You said: "Tetsu at the beginning wanted to live an insane life even if it's for a day, no matter the path"
This is BRILLIANT character conflict.
________________________________________
TETSU'S INTERNAL CONTRADICTION:
BEGINNING (Chapters 1-20):
Young Tetsu (pre-Collision):
•	Dead-end life, going nowhere
•	Watches others live freely while he's stuck
•	Internal desire: "I want to do something INSANE. Something that matters. Even if it destroys me."
•	"I want to feel ALIVE, even if it's just once."
•	Thinks about crime, violence, rebellion—anything to FEEL
•	But always backs down (fear, morality, paralysis)
The Collision happens:
•	The split occurs
•	The Other is BORN from this suppressed desire
•	The reckless, "fuck it" part of Tetsu becomes REAL
•	Host: Rational, cautious, wants to do good
•	Other: Instinctive, reckless, wants to LIVE
Early Story (Acts 1-2):
•	They work together (reluctantly)
•	The Other keeps them alive
•	Host keeps them moral
•	Tetsu thinks: "We're learning to coexist"
________________________________________
THE DIVERGENCE (Mid-Act 3):
After Jiro's Death + Father's Rescue (Ch 95-100):
Tetsu (Host) has revelation:
•	"We've been fighting for others. Protecting people. Doing GOOD."
•	"Jiro died doing good. Yuki died doing good. Father suffered for years doing good."
•	"And what did it bring us? Pain. Loss. Suffering."
•	BUT Tetsu chooses to continue anyway
•	"It's still worth it. Doing right matters, even when it hurts."
•	Becomes fully committed to being a HERO
The Other observes this:
•	Watches Tetsu choose sacrifice over self
•	Watches him cry over losses
•	Watches him carry guilt
•	Realizes: "This isn't what WE wanted."
The Other remembers:
•	Original Tetsu's dream: "Live insanely, feel alive, no regrets"
•	Current Tetsu: Carrying everyone's burdens, guilt-ridden, self-sacrificing
•	The Other: "This isn't LIVING. This is DYING slowly for others."
________________________________________
THE CONFRONTATION (Internal - Ch 98):
After battle. Tetsu exhausted, bandaged.

The Other: (internally) "We need to talk."

Tetsu: (internally) "Not now. I'm tired."

The Other: "That's the problem. You're always tired. Always hurting. Always sacrificing."

Tetsu: (internally) "That's what heroes do."

The Other: "FUCK being a hero."

Tetsu: (internally, shocked) "What?"

The Other: "You remember what you wanted? Before all this?"

Tetsu: (internally) "...That was childish. I've grown—"

The Other: "You've been BEATEN DOWN. You wanted to live insanely. To feel ALIVE. Now you just feel PAIN."

Tetsu: (internally) "People need us—"

The Other: "People DRAIN us. We give and give and they TAKE and someone always dies and you always CRY—"

Tetsu: (internally) "So what? I should stop caring?"

The Other: "You should start LIVING."

Tetsu: (internally) "I AM living—"

The Other: "No. You're ENDURING. There's a difference."

Silence.

The Other: "I was born from your desire to break free. To live without fear. To take what you want."

Tetsu: (internally) "That's not who I am anymore."

The Other: "It's who I STILL AM. And I'm tired of being dragged down by your guilt."

Tetsu: (internally) "...What are you saying?"

The Other: "I'm saying maybe we shouldn't be together anymore."
________________________________________
THE SEPARATION EVENT (Ch 100-102):
How It Happens:
During final Sanctum battle, something breaks:
The Scenario:
•	Massive fight, Tetsu pushing beyond limits
•	Trying to save everyone (civilians, team, even enemy Resolvers who want to surrender)
•	The Other: "Let them DIE. Focus on winning."
•	Tetsu: (internally) "No. We save everyone we can."
•	The Other: "This is EXACTLY the problem—"
Tetsu takes massive damage protecting a Sanctum soldier who ATTACKED THEM EARLIER.
The Other: "THAT'S IT. I'M DONE."
Something SNAPS in the dual cores.
The Fractured One's power activates unconsciously:
•	Tetsu carries their Resolve fragment
•	That fragment's ability: PERFECT SEPARATION
•	Cores split completely
•	The Other manifests as SEPARATE PHYSICAL BODY
________________________________________
THE SEPARATION SCENE:
Purple energy EXPLODES from Tetsu.

Tetsu: "What's happening—"

Pain. Blinding, searing pain.

The dual cores RIP APART.

Blue core stays in Tetsu.
Red core EJECTS.

The red energy forms a body beside him.

PHYSICAL. REAL. BREATHING.

The team stares.

Sara: "What the fuck—"

**The Other stands there. Same face as Tetsu. Red eyes. Manic grin.**

The Other: "Finally. FINALLY."

Tetsu: (on knees, gasping) "What did you—"

The Other: "I'm FREE. I'm ME. Not US anymore. ME."

Tetsu: "You can't— We're supposed to—"

The Other: "I'm done being your LEASH. Done being the part of you that you're ASHAMED OF."

Tetsu: "I'm not ashamed—"

The Other: "LIAR. You hate what I make you do. You hate that you NEED me."

Tetsu: "That's not—"

The Other: "I wanted to LIVE. You wanted to be a MARTYR. We're not the same."

Starts walking away.

Tetsu: "Where are you going?!"

The Other: (looking back) "Anywhere but here."

Crimson blade manifests in his hand.

The Other: "I'm going to do what YOU never had the balls to do."

Tetsu: "Which is?"

The Other: "Whatever the FUCK I want."

Gone.

Tetsu collapses. Feels empty. Incomplete.

Kaito: "Son—"

Tetsu: (whispering) "He left me. Again. Everyone leaves..."

Passes out.
________________________________________
THE OTHER'S NEW PATH (Acts 3-4):
What He Does:
Immediately After:
•	Revels in freedom (fights for fun, takes what he wants, lives recklessly)
•	"This is what LIVING feels like"
•	No guilt, no hesitation, no martyrdom
First Month Solo:
•	Becomes mercenary/vigilante hybrid
•	Takes jobs that pay well (morality questionable)
•	Kills without hesitation when "necessary"
•	"I'm not evil. I'm just HONEST."
But:
•	Feels... hollow
•	Freedom isn't as satisfying as he thought
•	Remembers the team, the apartment, Ayumi
•	"Why do I keep thinking about them?"
The Realization:
•	He's not "living" - he's just existing without consequences
•	The bonds he formed MATTERED
•	But going back means becoming Tetsu's "leash" again
•	Stuck: Can't return, can't move forward
________________________________________
THE OTHER BECOMES ANTAGONIST (Twist):
Joins a Faction:
•	NOT The Sanctum (too controlling)
•	A new group: "The Unchained" 
o	Ruptured who reject Resolver system
o	Believe in total freedom, no rules
o	Mix of genuine idealists and dangerous anarchists
o	Leader: [New character, Grade 1]
The Other's Role:
•	Becomes their top enforcer
•	"Finally, people who understand"
•	Fights AGAINST Resolvers (including Division 7)
First Re-encounter (Ch 115):
Division 7 responding to Unchained attack.

Tetsu arrives on scene.

Sees HIM standing there.

The Other: (grinning) "Miss me?"

Tetsu: "...You joined THEM?"

The Other: "They don't ask me to be anything I'm not."

Tetsu: "They're terrorists—"

The Other: "They're FREE. Something you'll never be."

Tetsu: "Come back. Please. We can—"

The Other: "There is no WE. Not anymore."

Attacks.

**Tetsu vs The Other: First Battle**

EVENLY MATCHED.

Tetsu (Blue Core): Foresight, prediction, defense
The Other (Red Core): Momentum, aggression, offense

**Neither can win.**

The Other: "See? We NEED each other. And I HATE that."

Tetsu: "Then stop fighting me!"

The Other: "I'd rather die free than live as your SHADOW."

Escapes.

Tetsu breaks down: "I lost myself. Literally."
