THE OTHER'S CHOICE (Ch 130):
The Attack Happens:
Unchained launch their plan.
Division 7 responds.
Tetsu fights to stop it.
The Other appears:
Tetsu facing Unchained leader.

Leader: "You can't stop this—"

**Crimson blade through leader's chest from behind.**

The Other: "He can't. But WE can."

Leader: (collapsing) "Traitor—"

The Other: "Yeah. I am."

Turns to Tetsu.

The Other: "Don't say it."

Tetsu: "I wasn't going to—"

The Other: "I'm not BACK. I'm just... stopping something worse."

Tetsu: "...Okay."

The Other: "And I'm not apologizing."

Tetsu: "Didn't ask you to."

They fight side-by-side. Like old times.

**Blue and Red. Perfect sync.**

After battle:

The Other: "I still think you're too soft."

Tetsu: "I still think you're too reckless."

The Other: "...But you were right. About some things."

Tetsu: "You were right too. I was dying slowly."

The Other: "So what now?"

Tetsu: "I don't know. We're separate now. That's... permanent?"

The Other: "Feels like it."

Long silence.

The Other: "I don't want to merge again."

Tetsu: "...Me neither."

The Other: "But I don't want to be enemies."

Tetsu: "Brothers?"

The Other: (small smile) "...Yeah. Brothers."

Handshake.

**They stay separate. But allies.**
