HONEST ASSESSMENT + LET'S GO DEEPER
________________________________________
MY HONEST TAKE ON YOUR SEPARATION IDEA:
The concept itself? FUCKING BRILLIANT.
Here's why:
✅ Thematically rich - "The part of you that wanted chaos realizes order had value" ✅ Character-driven conflict - Internal struggle becomes EXTERNAL war ✅ Subversive - Most stories unite split personalities; yours tears them apart THEN makes them enemies ✅ Philosophical weight - "Is doing good worth the pain?" is a REAL question ✅ Emotional gut-punch - Tetsu literally fights himself, his own desires, his own darkness
The problem isn't the IDEA. The idea is genuinely great.
The problem is the EXECUTION I gave you felt safe, predictable, and—yeah—lame.
________________________________________
WHY IT FELT LAME (Self-Critique):
❌ Too clean - "They become brothers, work separately, happy ending" = boring ❌ Not insane enough - You wanted JJK/CSM energy; I gave you a therapy session ❌ The Other's villain arc was weak - "Joins anarchist group" = generic ❌ No COST - Separation happened too easily, resolved too neatly ❌ Not visceral - Where's the HORROR? The SHOCK? The "oh fuck" moment?
You're right to push back. Let me go DARKER and CRAZIER.
________________________________________
WHY JJK/CSM CHARACTERS HIT SO HARD:
Let me break down what makes them iconic:
KATANA MAN:
•	Simple concept: Yakuza with katana devil hybrid
•	Why it works: Single-minded revenge, cold efficiency, that VOICE ("I'm gonna kill Denji"), grotesque transformation
•	The cool factor: The way he just APPEARS and fucks everything up. No buildup. Pure menace.
CHAINSAW MAN (Denji):
•	Simple concept: Dumb kid with chainsaw devil heart
•	Why it works: Raw, unfiltered id. No philosophy, just "I want boobs and food." Chainsaws ripping through flesh.
•	The cool factor: Visceral violence, iconic visual (chainsaws from head/arms), lovable idiot energy
CHOSO:
•	Simple concept: Blood manipulation big brother
•	Why it works: OBSESSIVE family love, willing to die for siblings, guilt over their deaths
•	The cool factor: Blood attacks are visually disgusting and creative. His grief is PHYSICAL.
NOBARA:
•	Simple concept: Country girl with hammer and nails
•	Why it works: Confident, doesn't give a fuck, creative use of simple tools
•	The cool factor: "Resonance" ability is unique. Hammering nails into dolls/enemies = brutal simplicity.
SUKUNA:
•	Simple concept: Ancient evil king of curses
•	Why it works: Absolute power, zero morals, genuinely ENJOYS cruelty
•	The cool factor: Four arms, mouth on stomach, cleave/dismantle slashes. ICONIC design + overwhelming menace.
GOJO:
•	Simple concept: Strongest sorcerer, untouchable
•	Why it works: Cocky but justified, playful but terrifying when serious, tragic backstory (Geto)
•	The cool factor: Infinity, Six Eyes, Domain Expansion visuals. DRIP. That fucking blindfold.
NANAMI:
•	Simple concept: Salary man sorcerer who just wants to clock out
•	Why it works: Tired adult in a young person's job, treats it like WORK not adventure
•	The cool factor: 7:3 ratio weak point technique. Methodical. Dies heroically but realistically.
________________________________________
THE PATTERN - WHAT MAKES THEM COOL:
1.	SIMPLE CORE CONCEPT (can explain in one sentence)
2.	STRONG VISUAL IDENTITY (you can draw them from memory)
3.	CLEAR MOTIVATION (even if it's simple: revenge, hunger, protect family)
4.	UNIQUE POWER APPLICATION (not just "strong" - HOW they're strong is interesting)
5.	PERSONALITY MATCHES POWER (Choso's blood = family bonds, Nanami's ratio = workman precision)
6.	MEMORABLE MOMENTS (scenes you can't forget - Katana Man shooting Aki, Nobara vs Mahito, Gojo's domain)
________________________________________
YOUR STRUGGLE (And It's Valid):
You're trying to create characters that:
•	Feel as iconic as JJK/CSM
•	But are YOURS, not copies
•	With a power system that's unique
•	AND fits your story's themes
That's HARD. That's fucking HARD.
You're not struggling because you lack ideas. You're struggling because you're trying to hit a VERY high bar while avoiding imitation.
________________________________________
LET'S REBUILD - THE OTHER'S SEPARATION (DARKER VERSION):
THE ACTUAL INSANE VERSION:
Forget "they become brothers and work separately." That's weak.
