THE RESOLUTION (Not "Happy Ending"):
Option A: TRAGIC
•	The Fragmented can't be saved
•	Tetsu has to mercy-kill him
•	Absorbs the Red Core back into himself
•	But The Other's personality is GONE
•	Tetsu becomes whole, but ALONE inside his head
•	Final words: "I'm sorry I couldn't let you live."
•	Tetsu gains both powers but loses his other self forever
•	Ending: Stronger but emptier
Option B: CONTAINED
•	Scientists find a way to stabilize him (barely)
•	The Fragmented is kept in containment
•	Still dangerous, still unstable
•	Tetsu visits him (like Hannibal Lecter dynamic)
•	They talk through barriers
•	The Fragmented gives advice (knows Tetsu's mind)
•	Never free, never whole, but not dead
•	Sequel hook: he escapes
Option C: SACRIFICE
•	Final battle against Sanctum
•	The Fragmented appears
•	"I may be a monster... but I'm YOUR monster."
