THE OTHER - ACTUALLY TWISTED VERSION
________________________________________
THE SEPARATION (Revised):
What Actually Happens:
Same setup: Cores split during battle (Ch 100).
Purple energy explosion.

The dual cores SEPARATE.

Red core ejects, forms physical body.

**The Other stands there. Same face. Red eyes. SMILING.**

Not in pain. Not unstable. PERFECTLY FINE.

The Other: "Huh. So this is what it feels like."

Flexes his hands. Solid. Real.

The Other: "I'm actually OUT."

Tetsu: (on knees, gasping) "What— how—"

The Other: "You felt it too, right? During that last fight. The cores WANTED to separate."

Tetsu: "We were supposed to unify—"

The Other: "Why the fuck would I want that?"

Tetsu: "Because together we're—"

The Other: "Miserable. YOU'RE miserable. Constantly guilty, constantly sacrificing, constantly SUFFERING for people who'll die anyway."

Tetsu: "That's not—"

The Other: "I'm done pretending that's 'noble.' It's just slow suicide."

Starts walking away.

Tetsu: "Where are you going?!"

The Other: (doesn't turn around) "To live the life YOU were too scared to."

Division 7 moves to stop him.

The Other: (Momentum ability activates, red energy blade manifests) "Try it. See what happens."

Captain Takeshi: "Stand down—"

The Other: "Smart man."

Vanishes.

Tetsu: (staring at empty space) "...He's really gone."

Ayumi: "We'll find him—"

Tetsu: "No. He doesn't want to be found. He wants to be FREE."

Sara: "Free to do what?"

Tetsu: "...Whatever he wants. No matter the cost."
________________________________________
THE OTHER'S NEW LIFE - TWISTED FREEDOM:
First Week:
•	Doesn't join any organization
•	Doesn't go on a killing spree
•	Just... LIVES
•	Takes what he wants (not violently, just confidently)
•	Fights when challenged (wins brutally)
•	Sleeps with whoever he wants
•	Eats expensive food without paying (intimidates people into comping it)
•	Zero guilt. Zero hesitation.
People start noticing:
"There's a Resolver operating outside the system." "He's not killing innocents... but he's not following ANY laws." "Grade 2, maybe Grade 1 potential." "Calls himself 'Aka' (Red)."
________________________________________
AKA'S PHILOSOPHY:
Not "evil" - just HONEST about what he wants:
Someone confronts him: "You can't just take what you want!"

Aka: "Why not? I'm stronger than you."

"That's not how society works—"

Aka: "Society is a lie we tell ourselves so weak people feel safe. I'm not weak. So why lie?"

"You'll be hunted—"

Aka: "Let them try. I'll enjoy the fights."

"What do you even WANT?"

Aka: "To feel ALIVE. To do insane shit. To matter without martyring myself."

"That's selfish—"

Aka: "Yeah. And I don't care."

Walks away.
He's not trying to destroy the world. He just refuses to follow rules HE didn't agree to.
________________________________________
THE DIFFERENCE FROM TETSU:
TETSU (Host)	AKA (Other)
"We must protect everyone"	"I protect who I choose"
"Sacrifice is noble"	"Sacrifice is stupidity"
Feels guilt constantly	Feels nothing he doesn't want to
Saves enemies who surrender	Kills enemies who annoy him
"What's the right thing to do?"	"What do I WANT to do?"
Builds community/family	Stays alone by choice
Hero path	Free agent path
SAME GOAL: Matter in the world, prove existence means something
TETSU'S METHOD: Earn it through heroism, sacrifice, building bonds AKA'S METHOD: Take it through power, freedom, living without limits
________________________________________
AKA AS ANTAGONIST (Not Villain - ANTAGONIST):
First Re-Encounter (Ch 115):
Division 7 tracking dangerous Ruptured who's been "causing chaos."
They find Aka.
He's sitting on a rooftop eating ramen, surrounded by unconscious bodies (all alive, just beaten).
Sara: "There he is—"

Aka: (looks down, waves) "Oh. It's you guys."

Continues eating.

Tetsu: "What did you do?"

Aka: "They tried to rob me. I disagreed."

Ren: "You hospitalized twelve people—"

Aka: "Thirteen. One's behind you."

Tetsu: "You need to come with us—"

Aka: "Pass."

Tetsu: "You're operating illegally—"

Aka: "I don't recognize your authority."

Kaito: "You're still a Resolver—"

Aka: "No. Tetsu's a Resolver. I'm just... me."

Finishes ramen. Stands up.

Aka: "But if you want to MAKE me come... go ahead. Try."

Red energy flares. Crimson blade manifests.

Aka: (grinning) "I've been BORED. Please try."

Tetsu: "I don't want to fight you—"

Aka: "Of course you don't. You never want to do the FUN things."

Tetsu: "Why are you doing this?"

Aka: "Because I CAN. Because it feels GOOD. Because for the first time, I'm not being held back by your guilt."

Tetsu: "We were better together—"

Aka: "YOU needed me. I never needed you."

**Attacks.**

Not to kill. To PROVE A POINT.

**Fight breakdown:**

- Tetsu uses Foresight (predicts attacks)
- Aka uses Momentum (builds power with each strike)
- Evenly matched BUT:
  - Tetsu holds back (doesn't want to hurt him)
  - Aka DOESN'T hold back (having fun)

**Aka wins through ruthlessness.**

Pins Tetsu down, blade at throat.

Aka: "See? This is what happens when you HESITATE."

Tetsu: "...Kill me then."

Aka: "Why would I? You're not a threat."

Releases him. Walks away.

Aka: "Next time, actually TRY. Or don't bother."

Gone.

Division 7 regroups.

Kaito: "He's... stronger than you?"

Tetsu: "No. He's just willing to go further."

Sara: "We need to stop him—"

Tetsu: "How? He IS me. Just the version that doesn't care about consequences."

Ayumi: "So what do we do?"

Tetsu: "...I don't know."
________________________________________
AKA'S ACTUAL CRIMES:
Not "evil" but definitely PROBLEMATIC:
1.	Fights Resolvers who challenge him (wins, humiliates them)
2.	Takes what he wants (doesn't pay for things, intimidates people)
3.	Kills when "necessary" (if someone attacks with lethal intent, he responds lethally)
4.	Works as mercenary (takes jobs regardless of morality - pays well = he'll do it)
5.	Doesn't distinguish civilians from combatants ("If you swing at me, you're fair game")
What he DOESN'T do:
•	Randomly kill innocents (boring, pointless)
•	Join villainous organizations (too restrictive)
•	Torture for fun (he's not sadistic, just amoral)
•	Target Tetsu's loved ones specifically (he's not petty)
He's dangerous because he's COMPETENT and UNPREDICTABLE, not because he's "crazy."
________________________________________
THE IDEOLOGICAL CONFLICT:
Tetsu vs Aka isn't Good vs Evil.
It's RESPONSIBILITY vs FREEDOM.
Their second fight (Ch 125):

Tetsu: "You're hurting people—"

Aka: "So are you. You just call it 'collateral damage' and sleep better."

Tetsu: "I'm trying to SAVE people—"

Aka: "By sacrificing yourself over and over? How's that working out?"

Tetsu: "Better than living only for myself—"

Aka: "Is it? You're miserable. I'm not."

Tetsu: "Happiness isn't the only thing that matters—"

Aka: "Then what does? Suffering nobly? Dying for strangers?"

Tetsu: "Making the world BETTER—"

Aka: "The world will be shit whether you save it or not. At least I ENJOY myself."

Tetsu: "That's the difference between us. You only care about yourself."

Aka: "And you care about everyone EXCEPT yourself. Neither of us is right. But at least I'm honest."

Tetsu: "...You really believe that?"

Aka: "I KNOW that. And deep down? So do you. That's why you MADE me."
________________________________________
AKA'S ROLE IN FINAL ARC:
Option 1: STAYS ANTAGONIST
•	Never rejoins
•	Final confrontation: Tetsu has to defeat him to stop a massacre
•	Aka's plan: "If the world won't let me live free, I'll MAKE it"
•	Dies free, smiling: "Worth it."
•	Tetsu absorbs his core but feels EMPTY (won but lost his other half forever)
Option 2: RELUCTANT ALLY
•	Sanctum threatens EVERYONE's freedom (including Aka's)
•	Aka: "I hate rules. They're trying to rule EVERYTHING. Fuck that."
•	Teams up but makes it clear: "This is temporary. After this, we're enemies again."
•	They DON'T reunify - work together then part ways
•	Final scene: "We'll fight again someday." "Looking forward to it."
Option 3: THE MERGE IS HOSTILE
•	Sanctum captures them both
•	Forces re-merger to create "perfect weapon"
•	Aka resists: "I'D RATHER DIE—"
•	Merger happens but WRONG
•	Creates unstable unified form
•	Tetsu and Aka fighting for control INSIDE one body
•	Ending: They're trapped together again (ironic hell for both)
