WHY THIS WORKS PERFECTLY:
✅ Gradual descent - Not instantly evil, slow moral divergence ✅ Hits all at once - Accumulation of small choices leads to "oh fuck" realization ✅ Storytelling tension - Readers/viewers wonder "is he going bad?" before confirmation ✅ The letters callback - PERFECT character detail (Tetsu writing to himself = foreshadowing the split) ✅ Dream/mental link - Keeps their connection alive, shows they're STILL linked despite separation ✅ Reluctant ally arc - Classic "enemy of my enemy" that DOESN'T erase their conflict
