2. SPEED DEMON - "VELOCITY"
BASIC INFO:
Name: SHINJI HAYATE (早手 真司) Age: 21 (same as Tetsu) Grade: 2 Affiliation: Tenjin Academy rival → Independent Resolver
APPEARANCE:
•	Short, wiry build (5'6" - uses it to his advantage)
•	Platinum blonde hair, styled back
•	Always wears running shoes (custom Resolve-enhanced)
•	Track marks on arms/legs (from speed friction burns)
•	Goggles around neck (wears during high-speed)
•	VISUAL HOOK: Afterimages trail behind him constantly (like motion blur made real)
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION: "KINETIC CASCADE"
Conviction: "Victory belongs to the one who strikes first, fastest, always"
How it works:
•	BUILDS SPEED PROGRESSIVELY
•	Starts fight at normal human speed
•	Each second of continuous movement = +10% speed
•	After 24 SECONDS of uninterrupted movement: near-teleportation speed
•	WEAKNESS: If he stops moving for 3+ seconds, speed resets to baseline
The Gimmick:
•	Has to keep moving to maintain speed
•	Creates "speed zones" - areas he's circled multiple times become accelerated
•	Allies inside speed zones move faster too
•	Can "store" momentum in objects (throws knife, it accelerates over distance)
Signature Moves:
•	"Cascade Rush" - 100+ strikes in 2 seconds (at peak speed)
•	"Phantom Step" - Leaves solid afterimage clone that lasts 3 seconds
•	"Terminal Velocity" - MAX SPEED sacrifice move (tears his body apart, one-shot capability)
Combat Style:
•	Hit-and-run exclusively
•	NEVER stops moving (even standing still, he's shifting weight)
•	Taunts enemies to waste their time
•	Fights like a mosquito (annoying, everywhere, impossible to catch)
________________________________________
PERSONALITY:
•	Arrogant speedster archetype
•	"You're too slow. Everyone's too slow."
•	Talks FAST (annoying quirk - sentences run together)
•	Impatient with everything (strategies, explanations, social interaction)
•	Addiction to adrenaline/speed (withdrawal when not fighting)
•	Quirk: Taps fingers/feet constantly (can't stay still)
Relationship with Tetsu:
•	Training academy rivals
•	Shinji: "You THINK too much. Just MOVE."
•	Constantly challenges him to races/fights
•	Respects Tetsu's tactical mind but frustrated by his hesitation
•	After academy: Becomes reluctant ally/friend
•	Their dynamic: Speed vs Strategy
Character Arc:
•	Starts overconfident (speed solves everything)
•	Gets HUMILIATED by Grade 1 opponent who counters speed
•	Learns strategy from Tetsu (reluctantly)
•	Final form: Combines speed with tactics (devastating)
Why He's Cool:
•	Speed building mechanic is UNIQUE (not just "I'm fast")
•	24-second timer creates tension (viewers/readers count with him)
•	Afterimage visual is iconic
•	Arrogant speedster is always fun
•	Weakness (must keep moving) is exploitable
