Conviction: "Everything vibrates. I conduct the chaos."
How it works:
•	Manipulates sound waves/vibrations/frequencies
•	Can hear EVERYTHING in 100m radius
•	Creates sound-based attacks
•	Unique trait: "Resonance Sight" 
o	Sees the world through SOUND (echolocation on steroids)
o	Can "see" through walls by sound reflection
o	Blind enemies are useless against them (they see through sound anyway)
________________________________________
ABILITIES BREAKDOWN:
OFFENSIVE:
1.	"Shatter Frequency" 
o	Finds resonant frequency of objects/people
o	Vibrates them until they BREAK
o	Can shatter bones, glass, metal, Cores (if exposed)
2.	"Sonic Blade" 
o	Compresses sound waves into cutting edge
o	Invisible slashes (you hear the cut before you feel it)
o	Can slice through Resolve constructs
3.	"Deafening Chorus" 
o	Area attack: All sound within 50m amplifies to PAINFUL levels
o	Enemies' eardrums rupture, lose balance (inner ear damage)
o	Hibiki immune (headphones filter/protect)
4.	"Bass Drop" 
o	Low-frequency shockwave
o	Feels like getting hit by truck (pure pressure)
o	Can stop hearts if aimed precisely (lethal)
________________________________________
DEFENSIVE:
5.	"Silence Field" 
o	Creates zone of ZERO sound (perfect vacuum)
o	No communication, no hearing, no sound-based attacks work
o	Enemies panic (sensory deprivation)
6.	"Echo Clone" 
o	Creates sound-based illusions (fake footsteps, voices, fighting sounds)
o	Enemies fight ghosts while Hibiki repositions
7.	"Harmonic Shield" 
o	Sound waves vibrate at frequency that REPELS attacks
o	Bullets slow down/stop
o	Works on physical + Resolve attacks
________________________________________
SUPPORT:
8.	"Whisper Network" 
o	Sends voice directly to allies' ears (long-range communication)
o	Can relay information across battlefield
o	Perfect for coordinated strikes
9.	"Sound Mapping" 
o	Creates 3D sound map of environment
o	Detects hidden enemies, traps, ambushes
o	Shares map with team via devices
________________________________________
THE HEADPHONES - "MAESTRO SYSTEM"
Not just aesthetic - they're ESSENTIAL:
Functions:
1.	Filter Control - Protects from own attacks
2.	Frequency Analysis - Scans enemies for weaknesses
3.	Recording - Stores sounds for later playback/attacks
4.	Amplification - Boosts allies' voices (morale/commands)
Design:
•	Bulky (military-grade)
•	Glowing blue sound meter on sides
•	Wired (not wireless - more reliable)
•	If destroyed: Hibiki's powers become UNCONTROLLABLE (hurts self + allies)
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
ZONE CONTROLLER:
•	Stays mid-range
•	Sets up "sound traps" (delayed sonic attacks)
•	Reads battlefield through echolocation
•	Calls out enemy positions to team
•	Debuffs enemies (deafen, disorient, pain)
TACTICAL GENIUS:
•	Hears enemy conversations (even whispered)
•	Detects lies (voice stress analysis)
•	Predicts attacks (hears muscle tension/breathing changes)
WEAKNESS:
•	If headphones destroyed: Powers go berserk (attacks everyone)
•	Total silence (rare) negates powers
•	Strong enough physical attacks still work (can't dodge everything)
________________________________________
PERSONALITY:
THE DUALITY:
When headphones ON (99% of the time):
•	Calm, analytical, quiet
•	Speaks softly (hates loud noises ironically)
•	Observes more than participates
•	Cryptic (says things like "I hear your heartbeat skip - you're lying")
•	Socially distant (people find them UNSETTLING)
When headphones OFF (rare):
•	Sensory OVERLOAD
•	Hears EVERYTHING (can't filter)
•	Panicked, overwhelmed, vulnerable
•	Clings to nearest person (needs grounding)
•	"Make it STOP— too loud too loud—"
Quirks:
•	Always has music playing (drowns out world)
•	Taps fingers to beats constantly
•	Hums when thinking
•	Collects vinyl records (analog purist)
•	Catchphrase: "I hear you." (ominous when said in battle)
________________________________________
BACKSTORY SKETCH:
The Awakening:
•	Awakened Resolve during concert
•	Crowd noise became DEAFENING (heard every person's heartbeat, breath, thought)
•	Sensory overload nearly killed them
•	Collapsed, bleeding from ears
•	Woke up in hospital, could "see" through sound
The Headphones:
•	Built by Resolver R&D specifically for them
•	Without them: Can't function (constant agony)
•	With them: One of the best surveillance operatives
•	Trade-off they accepted
Why They Fight:
•	Wants to find "perfect silence" (place with NO sound)
•	Believes defeating Sanctum will give them peace
•	Tired of hearing the world scream
________________________________________
RELATIONSHIP WITH TETSU:
First meeting (Intelligence briefing):

Hibiki: (headphones on, eyes closed) "You're Tetsu Mikage."

Tetsu: "How did you—"

Hibiki: "I hear two heartbeats in your chest. You're the split-core."

Tetsu: "...That's unsettling."

Hibiki: "You have no idea."

Later, during mission:

Tetsu: "Can you hear where the enemy is?"

Hibiki: "Seventeen of them. Twelve on ground floor, five basement. One's injured—his breathing is shallow. Another's scared—I hear his hands shaking."

Tetsu: "That's... incredibly useful."

Hibiki: "It's a nightmare. But I'm good at it."

After battle:

Tetsu: "You okay?"

Hibiki: (headphones off briefly, overwhelmed) "Too loud— everything's too—"

Tetsu: (helps put headphones back on) "Better?"

Hibiki: (calming down) "...Yes. Thank you."

Tetsu: "Anytime."

Hibiki: "...You're kind. I hear it in your voice. Most people fear me."

Tetsu: "Your power's scary. You're not."

Hibiki: (small smile) "...I'll remember that sound."
Their Dynamic:
•	Tetsu is one of few who treats them NORMALLY
•	Hibiki becomes fiercely protective (hears when Tetsu's in danger before anyone)
•	Acts as early warning system for team
•	Rare friendship (they don't have many)
________________________________________
CHARACTER ARC:
THE SEARCH FOR SILENCE:
Act 1: Uses power reluctantly (it's torture but necessary) Act 2: Masters it (becomes essential to team) Act 3: LOSES HEADPHONES in battle
•	Powers go BERSERK
•	Attacks friend and foe
•	Nearly kills themselves (brain overload)
•	Team has to subdue them
Recovery:
Hospital. New headphones being built.

Hibiki (no headphones, restrained, sedated): "Kill me. Please. I can't— I hear EVERYTHING—"

Tetsu: "New ones are almost ready—"

Hibiki: "What if they break again? What if I hurt you? What if—"

Tetsu: "Then we'll build new ones. Again. And again. Forever if we have to."

Hibiki: (crying) "Why? I'm a weapon that hurts everyone—"

Tetsu: "You're a person. Who happens to have a weapon."

Hibiki: "...I wish I could hear silence. Just once."

Tetsu: "Maybe one day you will."

New headphones arrive. Hibiki puts them on.

Silence (filtered). Relief.

Hibiki: "...Thank you."
Final Arc:
•	Accepts they'll never have "true" silence
•	Finds peace in CONTROLLED sound instead
•	Final battle: Removes headphones VOLUNTARILY for 30 seconds
•	Uses full unfiltered power (devastating)
•	Puts them back before brain damage
•	"I chose the noise. That makes it bearable."
________________________________________
WHY HIBIKI IS COOL:
✅ Unique power - Sound manipulation is underused ✅ Visual - Music notes/sound waves as VISIBLE attacks ✅ Duality - Calm with headphones, chaos without ✅ Tragic element - Their power is also their curse ✅ Support role - Not just DPS, actual TACTICAL value ✅ The headphones - Iconic visual + critical weakness ✅ Gender ambiguity - Intentional design choice ✅ Catchphrase - "I hear you" is simple but MENACING in context
