24. KAGAMI TSUBASA - "THE REFLECTION"
BASIC INFO:
Name: KAGAMI TSUBASA (鏡 翼 - "Mirror Wings") Age: 23 Grade: 2 Affiliation: Resolver, specializes in reconnaissance and psychological warfare
APPEARANCE:
•	Androgynously beautiful (deliberately cultivated)
•	Long silver-white hair (reflects light like mirrors)
•	Heterochromia: One eye silver, one eye gold
•	Always wears reflective accessories (glasses, jewelry, metallic clothing)
•	Pale skin (almost porcelain-like)
•	VISUAL HOOK: Floating mirror shards orbit around them constantly (like satellites)
________________________________________
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION: "INFINITE REFLECTION"
Conviction: "Truth is what you see reflected. I control what you see."
How it works:
•	Creates mirrors from Resolve energy (any size, any angle)
•	Mirrors can reflect, trap, distort, or redirect
•	Unique trait: "Reality Reflection" 
o	Can trap people in mirror dimensions
o	What happens to reflection happens to original (voodoo mirror effect)
o	Can create "mirror worlds" (temporary pocket dimensions)
________________________________________
ABILITIES BREAKDOWN:
OFFENSIVE:
1.	"Shard Storm" 
o	Mirror fragments as projectiles
o	Each shard reflects enemy's attack back at them
o	Creates feedback loop (attack yourself infinitely)
2.	"Doppelgänger" 
o	Creates perfect mirror clones (not illusions - REAL copies)
o	Clones have 50% of original's power
o	Can create up to 7 simultaneously
o	If clone "dies," original takes 10% damage
3.	"Reflection Strike" 
o	Attacks through mirrors
o	Punches mirror → fist emerges from mirror behind enemy
o	Can chain attacks through multiple mirrors (impossible angles)
4.	"Mirror Trap: Narcissus Prison" 
o	Traps enemy in mirror dimension
o	Infinite reflections of themselves
o	Psychological torture (confront infinite versions of self)
o	Enemy must "accept" themselves to escape
________________________________________
DEFENSIVE:
5.	"Mirror Shield" 
o	Reflects attacks back at sender
o	Works on physical AND Resolve-based attacks
o	Perfect defense if positioned correctly
6.	"Refraction" 
o	Bends light around self (invisibility)
o	Can appear in multiple places via mirrors
o	Makes targeting nearly impossible
7.	"Mirror World" 
o	Creates pocket dimension (mirror maze)
o	Kagami controls all physics inside
o	Up is down, left is right, distance is meaningless
o	Escape only when Kagami allows or is defeated
________________________________________
SUPPORT:
8.	"Observer's Eye" 
o	Places mirrors anywhere (surveillance)
o	Can see through all mirrors simultaneously
o	Perfect for recon missions
9.	"Truth Reflection" 
o	Forces people to see their "true self" in mirror
o	Reveals hidden intentions/emotions
o	Can break mental conditioning/illusions
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
PSYCHOLOGICAL WARFARE SPECIALIST:
•	Fights by making enemies fight themselves
•	Uses mirrors to create confusion/paranoia
•	Rarely touches enemies directly (proxies do the work)
•	Wins through mental exhaustion, not physical
SETUP-HEAVY:
•	Places mirrors strategically before engagement
•	Turns battlefield into mirror maze
•	Enemies get lost, attack wrong targets, go insane
WEAKNESS:
•	Mirrors can be shattered (breaks concentration)
•	Total darkness negates reflection powers
•	Straightforward overwhelming force can break through (if you ignore illusions)
________________________________________
PERSONALITY:
THE NARCISSIST:
•	OBSESSED with beauty (own and others')
•	Constantly checking reflection (compulsive)
•	Judges people based on appearance first
•	Believes "beauty is truth, truth is beauty"
•	Vain but not shallow (understands inner beauty too)
THE PHILOSOPHER:
•	Fixates on "self" and identity
•	"Who are you when no one's watching?"
•	"What if your reflection is the REAL you?"
•	Fascinated by people who "can't face themselves"
THE PERFORMER:
•	Theatrical, dramatic, EXTRA
•	Everything is a performance
•	Speaks in metaphors about mirrors/reflections
•	Bows after victories ("Thank you for the audience")
Quirks:
•	Catchphrase: "Look at yourself. REALLY look." (before trapping in mirror)
•	Polishes mirrors constantly (OCD tendency)
•	Takes photos obsessively (capturing "perfect moments")
•	Cannot tolerate dirty mirrors (breaks concentration)
•	Refers to self in third person sometimes ("Kagami thinks...")
________________________________________
BACKSTORY:
The Awakening:
•	Grew up as "ugly duckling" (bullied for appearance)
•	Teenage glow-up (became beautiful)
•	Discovered people treated them COMPLETELY differently
•	Awakened Resolve during identity crisis: 
o	"Who am I? The 'ugly' me or the 'beautiful' me?"
o	Stared at mirror for hours trying to figure it out
o	Resolve manifested: Infinite reflections appeared
o	"I'm ALL of them. Every version. Every possibility."
The Obsession:
•	Became obsessed with reflections/identity
•	Joined Resolvers to "help people face themselves"
•	Uses powers to force self-reflection (literally)
•	Genuinely believes they're HELPING people
•	"You can't grow until you accept what you see in the mirror."
________________________________________
RELATIONSHIP WITH TETSU:
First meeting (Joint mission):

Kagami: (circling Tetsu, studying) "Fascinating..."

Tetsu: "...What?"

Kagami: "You have TWO reflections. I've never seen that before."

Tetsu: "What are you talking about?"

Kagami: "In my mirrors, most people show one reflection. You show TWO. The you that hesitates... and the you that doesn't."

Tetsu: (uncomfortable) "That's just—"

Kagami: "Your Other. I can SEE him. Even when he's quiet."

The Other: (internally) "I don't like this person."

Tetsu: (internally) "Yeah. Me neither."

---

Later, during battle:

Kagami uses Mirror Trap on enemy.

Enemy (screaming inside mirror dimension): "Get me OUT—"

Tetsu: "Let them go—"

Kagami: "Not until they ACCEPT what they see."

Tetsu: "This is torture—"

Kagami: "This is THERAPY. There's a difference."

Enemy breaks (accepts themselves), released.

Kagami: "See? They're better now."

Tetsu: "...You're insane."

Kagami: (smiling) "Perhaps. But I'm BEAUTIFULLY insane."

---

After Aka separates:

Kagami: (excited) "You DID it! You became TWO!"

Tetsu: "It's not a good thing—"

Kagami: "It's INCREDIBLE. Most people spend their lives trying to integrate their shadow self. You FREED yours."

Tetsu: "He's becoming a monster—"

Kagami: "Or you're both becoming WHOLE. Separately."

Tetsu: "That doesn't make sense—"

Kagami: "The mirror doesn't lie, Tetsu. There are two of you. Always have been. Now everyone can see it."

Tetsu: "...I hate that you might be right."
Their Dynamic:
•	Kagami sees Tetsu as "perfect subject" (literal split personality)
•	Tetsu finds them unsettling but useful
•	Kagami offers psychological insights (unwanted but accurate)
•	Acts as therapist/tormentor hybrid
________________________________________
CHARACTER ARC:
THE SHATTERED REFLECTION:
Setup:
•	Kagami's power relies on self-acceptance
•	They preach it but haven't achieved it themselves
•	Still running from "ugly" past self
Crisis (Major battle):
•	Enemy with anti-reflection power (shadow manipulation?)
•	Destroys all Kagami's mirrors
•	Forces Kagami to see themselves WITHOUT reflection
•	Panic attack: "I can't see myself— I don't know who I AM—"
Rock Bottom:
Kagami (breaking down): "I need a mirror— PLEASE—"

Tetsu: "You don't need a mirror to know who you are—"

Kagami: "YES I DO— Without reflection I'm NOTHING—"

Tetsu: "You're Kagami. That's enough."

Kagami: "You don't UNDERSTAND— I built myself on reflections— Without them I'm still that ugly, worthless—"

Tetsu: "You're not."

Kagami: "How do you KNOW—"

Tetsu: "Because I see you. Not your reflection. YOU."

Kagami: (crying) "...What do you see?"

Tetsu: "Someone who helps people face themselves because you're still learning to face yourself. Someone who's beautiful because you CHOSE to be. Not because a mirror told you."

Kagami: (breaking down completely) "I'm so tired of performing..."

Tetsu: "Then stop. Just be Kagami. That's enough."
Resolution:
•	Fights without mirrors (learns to trust self without reflection)
•	Powers evolve: Can create reflections from MEMORY, not just mirrors
•	Accepts all versions of self (past, present, future)
•	Final form: "True Reflection" - sees self clearly, no distortion
________________________________________
WHY KAGAMI IS COOL:
✅ Mirror powers - Visually stunning, versatile ✅ Psychological warfare - Not just combat, MENTAL attacks ✅ Narcissist with depth - Vain but struggling with identity ✅ Philosophical - Asks real questions about self/identity ✅ Visual hook - Orbiting mirror shards + heterochromia ✅ Tragedy - Beauty built on insecurity ✅ Unique weakness - No reflection = identity crisis
________________________________________
________________________________________
25. RAIDEN KAITO - "STORM HERALD"
BASIC INFO:
Name: RAIDEN KAITO (雷電 海斗 - "Thunder-Lightning Sea-Fighter") Age: 19 Grade: 1 Affiliation: Tenjin Academy prodigy, Division 3 (Rapid Response)
APPEARANCE:
•	Medium height, athletic build (lean muscle)
•	Spiky black hair (LITERALLY stands up from static electricity)
•	Bright yellow eyes (glow when powers active)
•	Burn scars on palms/fingertips (from early power use)
•	Wears rubber-soled boots (grounding)
•	Sleeveless vest (arms free for better conductivity)
•	VISUAL HOOK: Electricity CONSTANTLY arcs between fingers, hair, even when "calm"
________________________________________
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION: "TEMPEST DOMINION"
Conviction: "I am the storm. Unstoppable, untouchable, ABSOLUTE."
How it works:
•	Generates electricity from body
•	Can absorb/redirect external electricity
•	Nervous system runs on overclocked bioelectricity
•	Unique trait: "Storm Brain" 
o	Thinks FASTER than normal humans (electricity speeds neural signals)
o	Processes information at 10x speed
o	Reaction time: 0.01 seconds
________________________________________
ABILITIES BREAKDOWN:
OFFENSIVE:
1.	"Lightning Strike" 
o	Classic lightning bolt from hand/sky
o	Can chain between enemies (arcs to nearest target)
o	Stronger when fighting multiple opponents
2.	"Railgun" 
o	Throws metal object (coin, nail, etc.)
o	Accelerates it with electromagnetic force
o	Hypersonic projectile (punches through anything)
3.	"Thunder Clap" 
o	Claps hands together
o	Creates sonic boom + electromagnetic pulse
o	Stuns enemies, fries electronics
4.	"Storm Blade" 
o	Electricity shaped into sword/spear
o	Cuts AND electrocutes
o	Can extend length at will
5.	"Overload" 
o	Touches enemy directly
o	Pumps electricity into their nervous system
o	Causes seizures, paralysis, cardiac arrest (lethal)
________________________________________
DEFENSIVE:
6.	"Lightning Armor" 
o	Wraps body in electricity
o	Auto-shocks anyone who touches
o	Increases speed (muscles stimulated)
7.	"Electromagnetic Barrier" 
o	Creates magnetic field
o	Repels metal objects
o	Slows/stops projectiles
8.	"Flash Step" 
o	Converts body to electricity briefly
o	Travels through conductive materials (wires, metal, water)
o	Near-teleportation (within conductive network)
________________________________________
UTILITY:
9.	"Hack" 
o	Can interface with electronics via touch
o	Overrides security, steals data, crashes systems
o	EMP on demand (destroys enemy tech)
10.	"Defibrillator" 
o	Can restart hearts (ally support)
o	Shock someone back to consciousness
o	Dangerous (could kill if wrong voltage)
11.	"Storm Call" 
o	Creates actual storm clouds (takes time)
o	Unlimited lightning source once active
o	Weather manipulation (limited)
________________________________________
THE SPEED BOOST - "OVERDRIVE"
His Signature Technique:
By overclocking his nervous system with electricity:
•	Perception slows (world moves in slow-motion to him)
•	Movement speeds up (near-teleportation speed)
•	Thinking accelerates (solves problems instantly)
At Overdrive:
•	Can dodge bullets AFTER they're fired
•	Lands 50+ hits per second
•	Reads opponents like books (sees micro-expressions)
Cost:
•	Burns through stamina FAST (3-5 minutes max)
•	Muscle damage (tearing from overexertion)
•	Neural fatigue (brain overheats, nosebleeds, blackouts)
•	Addiction risk (feels ALIVE in Overdrive, dull normally)
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
BLITZ FIGHTER:
•	Overwhelms with SPEED + POWER combo
•	Doesn't give enemies time to think
•	Strikes from multiple angles rapidly
•	Finishes fights in under 60 seconds (if possible)
TERRAIN CONTROL:
•	Uses metal/water in environment (conducts electricity)
•	Creates electric fields (enemies take damage just by proximity)
•	Can fight from range OR close-quarters
WEAKNESS:
•	Rubber/insulators negate powers
•	Earth/grounding dissipates electricity
•	Exhausts quickly (high output = high cost)
•	Can't use phones/electronics normally (fries them)
________________________________________
PERSONALITY:
THE HYPERACTIVE GENIUS:
•	TALKS EXTREMELY FAST (thinks fast, speaks fast)
•	Sentences run together
•	Interrupts people constantly (brain moves faster than conversation)
•	Easily bored (needs stimulation constantly)
•	Can't sit still (fingers tap, leg bounces, always moving)
THE ADRENALINE JUNKIE:
•	Addicted to speed/danger/fighting
•	"Normal life is BORING"
•	Takes unnecessary risks (just to feel alive)
•	Withdrawal when not fighting (depression, lethargy)
THE SHOWOFF:
•	Cocky, arrogant, flashy
•	"I'm the fastest AND the strongest"
•	Loves audience (does unnecessary tricks mid-fight)
•	But backs it up (actually IS that good)
Quirks:
•	Catchphrase: "You blinked. You lost." (fights end before enemies react)
•	Snaps fingers constantly (creates sparks)
•	Wears sunglasses indoors (eyes glow, bothers people)
•	Eats TONS (high metabolism from electricity generation)
•	Can't sleep easily (brain too active)
________________________________________
BACKSTORY:
The Awakening:
•	Child prodigy (genius-level IQ)
•	But also ADHD (couldn't focus, constantly restless)
•	The Collision happened: 
o	Electricity surged through his body
o	Nervous system adapted, enhanced
o	Suddenly: Could think as fast as he wanted to
The Addiction:
•	First time using Overdrive: "This is what life should ALWAYS feel like"
•	Started using it constantly (even outside combat)
•	Crashed HARD (hospitalized from overuse)
•	Resolvers recruited him, taught control
•	Still struggles with wanting to live in Overdrive permanently
Why He Fights:
•	Only time he feels ALIVE
•	Normal life is "slow motion"
•	Needs combat/danger to function
•	Searching for opponent who can keep up
