26. SUMI HARUKA - "THE CALLIGRAPHER"
BASIC INFO:
Name: SUMI HARUKA (墨 遥 - "Ink Distant/Far-reaching") Age: 27 Grade: 2 Affiliation: Resolver, specializes in support and tactical operations
APPEARANCE:
•	Tall, elegant build
•	Long black hair in traditional style (bun with chopstick pins)
•	Wears modified traditional clothing (hakama pants, haori jacket)
•	Ink stains on fingers ALWAYS (even when not fighting)
•	Carries calligraphy brush (heirloom, ornate)
•	Reading glasses (nerdy aesthetic)
•	VISUAL HOOK: Ink flows from fingertips constantly, forms characters/symbols in air
________________________________________
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION: "KOTOBA NO CHIKARA" (Power of Words)
Conviction: "Words shape reality. I write the world as it should be."
How it works:
•	Uses ink as medium for Resolve
•	Writes kanji/words in air (they become REAL effects)
•	Unique trait: "Linguistic Reality Manipulation" 
o	Words written = commands to reality
o	Specific kanji = specific effects
o	Can combine characters for complex effects
________________________________________
THE SYSTEM - HOW INK WRITING WORKS:
BASICS:
1.	Writes in air with finger/brush (ink manifests from Resolve)
2.	Kanji appears (glowing, floating, 3D)
3.	Effect activates based on meaning
4.	Duration: Simple words = instant, complex = setup time
5.	Cost: More complex kanji = more Resolve drain
LIMITATIONS:
•	Can only write kanji they KNOW (memorized vocabulary = power ceiling)
•	Must write CORRECTLY (one stroke wrong = no effect)
•	Takes TIME to write complex characters (vulnerable during)
•	Can maintain max 7 active words simultaneously
•	Opponent can "erase" ink (destroying the kanji cancels effect)
________________________________________
ABILITY CATEGORIES:
OFFENSIVE KANJI:
1.	炎 (Fire) 
o	Flames erupt where written
o	Can write on surfaces (wall burns) or air (fireball)
2.	雷 (Thunder/Lightning) 
o	Lightning strikes from character
o	Written on enemy = direct shock
3.	刃 (Blade) 
o	Creates sword/cutting edge from ink
o	Flies toward target, slashes
4.	爆 (Explosion) 
o	Detonates on contact
o	Delayed fuse (write, it explodes after countdown)
5.	崩 (Collapse/Crumble) 
o	Structures written on FALL APART
o	Weakens materials/Resolve constructs
________________________________________
DEFENSIVE KANJI:
6.	壁 (Wall) 
o	Solid barrier appears
o	Strength depends on how well it's written
7.	盾 (Shield) 
o	Personal barrier around self or ally
o	Circular defense
8.	癒 (Heal) 
o	Accelerates recovery when written on wounds
o	NOT instant (gradual healing over minutes)
9.	封 (Seal) 
o	Binds/restricts movement
o	Written on enemy = paralysis
o	Can seal doors, containers, even abilities
________________________________________
UTILITY KANJI:
10.	視 (See/Vision) 
o	Written on wall = sees through it
o	Creates surveillance point
11.	聴 (Hear/Listen) 
o	Enhances hearing in area
o	Eavesdropping
12.	速 (Speed) 
o	Increases movement speed
o	Written on ally or self
13.	力 (Strength/Power) 
o	Temporary strength boost
o	Enhances physical capabilities
14.	飛 (Fly) 
o	Levitation/flight (limited duration)
o	Can write on objects to make them float
15.	隠 (Hide/Conceal) 
o	Invisibility/camouflage
o	Temporary stealth
________________________________________
ADVANCED/COMBINATION KANJI:
16.	炎雷 (Fire + Lightning) = "Plasma Burst" 
o	Combines effects (superheated lightning)
17.	刃風 (Blade + Wind) = "Cutting Gale" 
o	Wind blades that slice everything
18.	封印 (Seal + Mark) = "Binding Seal" 
o	Permanent seal (requires full ritual writing)
19.	生死 (Life + Death) = "Threshold" 
o	Can stabilize dying person OR finish off wounded (depending on intent)
20.	真実 (Truth + Reality) = "Manifest Truth" 
o	Forces truth (interrogation)
o	Makes lies physically painful to speak
________________________________________
ULTIMATE TECHNIQUE: "NARRATIVE REWRITE"
The Big One:
•	Writes FULL SENTENCE in air (not just single kanji)
•	Takes 30+ seconds (extremely vulnerable)
•	Creates COMPLEX reality manipulation
•	Example: "敵の力は消える" (The enemy's power disappears) = temporary ability nullification
•	Costs 50% of total Resolve (can only use 1-2 times per battle)
•	Must write perfectly (one error = catastrophic failure)
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
TACTICAL CALLIGRAPHER:
•	Setup Phase: Writes defensive/utility kanji before engagement
•	Mid-Range Fighter: Stays back, writes offensive kanji
•	Support Role: Buffs allies, debuffs enemies
•	Finisher: Narrative Rewrite for impossible situations
WEAKNESS:
•	Interrupted writing = wasted Resolve (vulnerable while writing)
•	Illiteracy of rare kanji (can't use what they don't know)
•	Physical destruction (ink can be erased/destroyed)
•	Speed users (can't write fast enough)
•	Close combat (brush makes melee difficult)
________________________________________
PERSONALITY:
THE SCHOLAR:
•	Calm, measured, intellectual
•	Speaks formally (uses keigo/honorifics constantly)
•	Loves literature, poetry, calligraphy
•	Philosophical about language/power
•	"Words have weight. Choose them carefully."
THE PERFECTIONIST:
•	OBSESSED with correct stroke order
•	Cannot tolerate grammatical errors
•	Corrects people's kanji mid-conversation
•	Rewrites documents that have mistakes
•	"If it's worth writing, it's worth writing CORRECTLY."
THE ARTIST:
•	Views combat as performance art
•	Choreographs fights (plans kanji sequences aesthetically)
•	Signs work after battles (literally signs name in ink on wall)
•	Critiques own performance harshly
Quirks:
•	Catchphrase: "Let me write you a story." (before major attack)
•	Carries multiple brushes (different sizes for different effects)
•	Practices calligraphy daily (meditation)
•	Cannot resist correcting typos (even enemy's)
•	Keeps diary in PERFECT handwriting
________________________________________
BACKSTORY:
The Tradition:
•	Born into family of master calligraphers (centuries-old lineage)
•	Trained from childhood in traditional arts
•	Father was renowned, expected Haruka to continue legacy
•	But Haruka wanted to be writer, not calligrapher
The Awakening:
•	During argument with father about future
•	"Words are just DECORATION! They don't DO anything!"
•	Haruka, in rage: Wrote 怒 (anger) in air with finger
•	The kanji EXPLODED
•	Room destroyed, father injured
•	Haruka: "...Words DO do something."
The Path:
•	Joined Resolvers (could use power constructively)
•	Studied kanji obsessively (more knowledge = more power)
•	Became master tactician (writes reality itself)
•	Still practices traditional calligraphy (respects father's art now)
