•	Must maintain aggression (no defensive moves break the chain)
•	Resets if he stops attacking for 3+ seconds
•	Gets STRONGER the longer he commits to offense
•	Requires recklessness (Host won't use it, too risky)
What makes it different:
•	MOMENTUM-based (builds up, not instant)
•	Rewards aggression (opposite of Host's calculated approach)
•	More dramatic (visible power escalation)
