CRIMSON BLADE - CLARIFICATION:
How it works:
Manifestation:
•	It's a Resolve energy construct (not a physical sword he carries)
•	Manifests from his right forearm/hand
•	Can summon/dismiss instantly (doesn't need to say anything)
•	Just extends from his arm when he wants it
Visual:
•	Red/black energy shaped like a blade
•	Extends from forearm (like an arm-mounted weapon)
•	Can be short (knife-length) or long (sword-length) depending on need
•	Glows brighter when using Momentum
•	Leaves crimson energy trail when swung
Combat use:
•	Close-range slashing weapon
•	Can extend reach mid-swing
•	Cuts through Resolve constructs easily
•	Gets sharper/stronger as Momentum builds
•	Dismisses instantly when not needed (doesn't stay manifested 24/7)
Think of it like:
•	Assassin's Creed hidden blade BUT made of energy
•	Tokyo Ghoul kagune blade BUT from forearm not back
•	Can appear/disappear at will (thought-activated)
________________________________________
RESOLVE ENERGY - CLARIFICATION:
You're right, I made an error. Let me fix:
HE DOES HAVE RESOLVE ENERGY (Limited Pool):
How Momentum works CORRECTLY:
•	He HAS a Resolve energy pool (like everyone)
•	Momentum ability: Consecutive attacks deal MORE DAMAGE without costing MORE Resolve
•	Essentially: Better efficiency/output from same energy cost
•	Gets "free" power scaling through aggression
Example:
•	1st punch: Costs 10 Resolve, deals 100 damage
•	5th punch (with Momentum): Still costs 10 Resolve, deals 300 damage
•	The DAMAGE increases, the COST doesn't
So he DOES tire out eventually:
•	Runs out of Resolve like everyone
•	Just gets more bang for his buck through Momentum
•	Can't fight forever (stamina/energy limits)
Black Surge specifically:
•	Uses significant Resolve to activate
•	Gets bonus damage from Momentum buildup
•	Can't spam it (each use costs energy)
NOT like: "Infinite power, fights forever, gets stronger infinitely" ACTUALLY: "Efficient damage scaling, but still has limits"
