KAITO NOMURA - FLAME COLOR OPTIONS
You're right. Orange/red fire is generic. Let's make it COOL.
________________________________________
FLAME COLOR OPTIONS:
________________________________________
OPTION 1: AZURE FLAMES (Blue)
Visual: Bright blue flames (hotter than normal fire) Symbolism: "Burning with pure protective intent" Science basis: Blue flames are actually hotter than red/orange Combat look: Striking contrast, ethereal, cold-burn aesthetic Protective Fury mode: Turns WHITE-BLUE (like lightning)
________________________________________
OPTION 2: GOLDEN FLAMES (Yellow-Gold)
Visual: Warm golden fire (like sunlight solidified) Symbolism: "Heart of gold" personality, warmth, heroic Aesthetic: Radiant, hopeful, inspiring Combat look: Bright, eye-catching, heroic energy Protective Fury mode: Turns PURE WHITE-GOLD (blinding)
________________________________________
OPTION 3: EMERALD FLAMES (Green)
Visual: Jade/emerald green fire (unnatural, striking) Symbolism: "Life/growth through fire" (phoenix rebirth energy) Aesthetic: Unique, mystical, rare Combat look: Eerie but beautiful, stands out completely Protective Fury mode: Turns WHITE-GREEN (searing)
________________________________________
OPTION 4: VIOLET FLAMES (Purple)
Visual: Deep purple/violet fire with pink highlights Symbolism: "Passion made manifest" Aesthetic: Royal, intense, emotional Combat look: Dramatic, otherworldly Protective Fury mode: Turns MAGENTA-WHITE (overwhelming)
________________________________________
OPTION 5: SOLAR FLAMES (Orange-White Core)
Visual: Orange flames with WHITE-HOT core (like the sun) Symbolism: "The sun: life-giver and destroyer" Aesthetic: Layered color (orange outside, white inside) Combat look: Realistic but INTENSE Protective Fury mode: PURE SOLAR WHITE (star-heat)
________________________________________
OPTION 6: OBSIDIAN FLAMES (Black with Orange/Red Edges)
Visual: Black flames with glowing edges (inverted fire) Symbolism: "Dark protector" (fights darkness with darkness) Aesthetic: Ominous but heroic, subverts expectations Combat look: EXTREMELY distinctive (black fire is rare in anime) Protective Fury mode: Black flames turn CRIMSON-CORE (rage unleashed)
________________________________________
OPTION 7: DUAL-TONE FLAMES (Split Color)
Visual: Flames shift colors based on emotion
•	Calm/Normal: Amber/Orange (warm, friendly)
•	Protective/Serious: AZURE BLUE (cold determination)
•	Fury/Desperate: WHITE (absolute) Symbolism: Emotional state visible through fire color Combat look: Dynamic, changes during fight
________________________________________
MY TOP 3 RECOMMENDATIONS:
________________________________________
#1: AZURE FLAMES (Blue)
Why it works:
•	Hotter than normal fire = matches his protective intensity
•	Visually STRIKING (blue fire stands out)
•	Contrast with Aka's red/black (different fire users, different colors)
•	Scientific backing (blue = hotter temperature)
•	White-blue Fury mode looks INCREDIBLE
Downsides:
•	Blue fire exists in other anime (Rin from Blue Exorcist, Endeavor's blue flames)
________________________________________
#2: GOLDEN FLAMES (Yellow-Gold)
Why it works:
•	Matches his personality (golden retriever = golden flames)
•	Warm, heroic, inspiring aesthetic
•	Different from typical red/orange
•	Pure white-gold Fury mode = blinding radiance
•	"Heart of gold burns bright" theme
Downsides:
•	Less "edgy," more straightforwardly heroic
________________________________________
#3: OBSIDIAN FLAMES (Black with colored edges)
Why it works:
•	EXTREMELY unique (black fire is rare)
•	Subverts "bright happy guy" expectation (depth to character)
•	Looks SICK in combat (dark flames = intimidating)
•	Could have orange/gold EDGES (keeps warmth while being unique)
•	Opens character arc: "Why are his flames black? Is he hiding darkness?"
Downsides:
•	Black flames usually associated with "evil" (might confuse audience initially)
________________________________________
HYBRID OPTION (My Personal Favorite):
AMBER-CORE AZURE FLAMES
Visual:
•	Outer flames: Bright AZURE BLUE (hot, protective)
•	Inner core: AMBER-GOLD (warmth, his true heart)
•	Effect: Looks like blue fire with golden heart
Symbolism:
•	Blue = His determination/strength (what people see)
•	Gold = His kindness/warmth (what's inside)
•	"Strong exterior, warm interior"
Protective Fury Mode:
•	Core expands (more gold visible)
•	Blue intensifies to WHITE-BLUE
•	Looks like a STAR (golden core with white-blue corona)
Why this works:
•	UNIQUE (two-tone fire)
•	Character-appropriate (shows duality)
•	Visually STUNNING
•	Different from everyone
________________________________________
QUICK COMPARISON:
Color	Uniqueness	Fits Personality	Visual Impact	Symbolism
Azure Blue	7/10	8/10	9/10	Protective heat
Golden	8/10	10/10	8/10	Heart of gold
Obsidian Black	10/10	5/10	10/10	Hidden depth
Amber-Azure	10/10	9/10	10/10	Duality
________________________________________
MY RECOMMENDATION:
Go with AMBER-CORE AZURE (hybrid option)
Why:
•	Nobody else has this
•	Fits his character perfectly (warm heart, strong protector)
•	Looks AMAZING (blue and gold together)
•	Fury mode is visually distinct
•	Gives him depth (not just "fire guy")
OR if you want simpler:
Pure AZURE BLUE flames (clean, hot, protective)
