________________________________________
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION:
Type: Conversion (energy transformation)
Conviction: "I turn suffering into peace. No one dies on my watch."
How it works:
•	Converts Resolve energy into healing
•	Can also REVERSE it (convert life force into attack - desperate only)
•	Primarily support, reluctant fighter
________________________________________
ABILITIES:
1. LIFE EXCHANGE (Primary Healing)
•	Touches wounded ally
•	Converts their injury into dissipating energy
•	Wound "evaporates" into golden light
•	Cost: Uses his Resolve, drains him
•	Limit: Can't heal fatal wounds (only stabilize)
2. REGENERATION FIELD
•	Creates 5m radius healing zone
•	Allies inside slowly regenerate (passive healing)
•	Can maintain for 10 minutes max
•	Cost: Continuous Resolve drain
3. PAIN TRANSFER
•	Takes ally's pain into himself
•	They feel nothing, he feels EVERYTHING
•	Allows them to keep fighting
•	Cost: He experiences their agony (horrible but effective)
4. VITAL SURGE
•	Emergency healing burst
•	Touches dying ally, floods them with life energy
•	Can pull them from death's edge
•	Cost: 50% of his Resolve, leaves him vulnerable
5. DESPERATE REVERSAL (Last Resort)
•	REVERSES his ability
•	Converts his life force INTO explosive attack
•	One massive blast of golden energy
•	Cost: Nearly kills him, needs immediate treatment after
•	Only uses if team will die otherwise
6. DIAGNOSIS
•	Passive ability (always active)
•	Can "see" injuries, illnesses, Core damage
•	Knows exactly what's wrong and how to fix it
•	Makes him invaluable support
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
•	Non-combatant preference (stays back, heals)
•	Defensive only (will fight to protect, won't initiate)
•	Support role (enables team to fight harder/longer)
•	Last resort attacker (Desperate Reversal only when no choice)
Weakness:
•	Hates fighting (hesitates in combat)
•	Prioritizes healing over self-defense
•	Will sacrifice himself for team (self-destructive tendency)
________________________________________
STORY ROLE:
Training Arc:
•	Helps injured trainees
•	Bonds with Tetsu (both struggle with "doing enough")
•	Teaches basic first aid to squad
Division 7:
•	Team medic (most important role)
