HONEST ASSESSMENT
________________________________________
TAKESHI'S TACTICAL COMMANDMENT ABILITY:
What I Think:
PROS:
•	✅ Conceptually interesting (battlefield becomes game board)
•	✅ Unique mechanics (role assignment, zone control)
•	✅ Fits his character (military tactician)
•	✅ Team-oriented (actually useful for leadership)
•	✅ Visual appeal (grid patterns, glowing roles)
CONS:
•	❌ Maybe TOO complicated (lots of moving parts)
•	❌ Could be hard to illustrate in manga/anime (busy visual)
•	❌ Might slow down combat pacing (too many rules)
•	❌ Less immediately "cool" than simpler powers
MY HONEST TAKE:
It's SMART but maybe not EXCITING enough for a captain-level character.
Compare to JJK:
•	Gojo: Infinity (instantly understood, visually sick)
•	Sukuna: Slashes (simple, brutal, iconic)
•	Higuruma: Trial domain (complex BUT has clear dramatic payoff - guilty/not guilty verdict)
Takeshi's ability is complex WITHOUT a clear dramatic "moment" that makes you go "HOLY SHIT"
