•	The Arbiter (the assassin who killed Fractured One) survived
•	They're working through the Sanctum
•	Tetsu is THEIR backup plan
•	Tetsu carries a "kill switch" in his Resolve
•	When activated: He becomes an unstoppable weapon for the Sanctum
•	His entire existence is a SLEEPER AGENT program
•	Aka's separation was him trying to BREAK FREE of the programming
Why this is shocking:
•	✅ Tetsu could become the final boss
•	✅ His heroic journey might be for nothing
•	✅ Makes every victory bittersweet (leading to his activation)
•	✅ Aka becomes the HERO (trying to save Tetsu from himself)
________________________________________
OPTION D: THE OTHER IS FROM THE FUTURE
The Twist:
•	Aka isn't a split personality from The Collision
•	Aka is Tetsu from a PREVIOUS TIMELINE
•	He time-looped back to prevent a catastrophe
•	The "voice in Tetsu's head" was future-him trying to guide past-him
•	The Collision created a paradox that made future-Tetsu manifest physically
•	He's been trying to change fate but can't tell present-Tetsu without breaking causality
Why this is shocking:
•	✅ Explains Aka's knowledge/instincts (he's lived this before)
•	✅ His "recklessness" is desperation (knows what's coming)
•	✅ Makes their conflict TRAGIC (fighting himself across time)
•	✅ Opens time loop/destiny themes
