OPTION E: THERE IS NO "OTHER" - TETSU IS INSANE
The Twist (Dark):
•	Aka doesn't exist
•	Tetsu has severe dissociative identity disorder
•	The Collision traumatized him so badly he created "The Other"
•	When Aka "takes control," it's just Tetsu in a different mental state
•	The "separation" was a psychotic break
•	Aka walking around is HALLUCINATION - others see only Tetsu
•	Everything Aka "does" is actually Tetsu's actions he can't accept
Why this is shocking:
•	✅ Completely subverts supernatural elements
•	✅ Makes story a psychological horror
•	✅ Everything becomes unreliable narrator
•	✅ DEEPLY disturbing
BUT: This might be TOO dark and undermines the cool powers/action
