MY RECOMMENDATION FOR ACTUAL MIND-BLOWING TWIST:
OPTION B (Tetsu died, Aka is the original) + OPTION C elements (programming/kill switch)
Combined Twist:
•	Original Tetsu died in The Collision
•	Aka (survivor) created "Tetsu" personality as coping mechanism
•	But ALSO: The Sanctum implanted commands in Aka during the Collision
•	Aka KNOWS he's programmed (that's why he separated - trying to break free)
•	"Tetsu" doesn't know he's not real
•	Final arc: Aka must choose - save Tetsu (who's not real) or save himself (who's compromised)
Why this works:
•	✅ TWO twists (identity swap + programming)
•	✅ Makes separation tragic (Aka trying to save them both)
•	✅ Questions reality/identity constantly
•	✅ No clear "good" answer
•	✅ Explains EVERYTHING retroactively
