- Tetsu fighting a major threat (maybe Void? Or Sanctum agent?)
- Pushing himself beyond limits
- Cores overheating, unstable
- The Other takes over to finish the fight

MID-BATTLE:
- Aka (as The Other) goes TOO HARD
- Cores can't handle the strain
- Energy starts FRACTURING

TETSU (internally): "What's happening—"

AKA: "I don't know— Something's WRONG—"

Purple energy (their unified color) starts SPLITTING.

Silver and black/crimson separating VIOLENTLY.

TETSU: "Stop— We need to—"

AKA: "I CAN'T— I CAN'T STOP IT—"

EXPLOSION. Blinding light.

---

AFTERMATH:
- Smoke clears
- TWO BODIES on the ground
- Tetsu (silver eyes, gasping)
- Aka (black eyes, coughing)

They see each other. PHYSICALLY separate.

Tetsu: "...What did you do?"

Aka: "ME?! You're the one who—"

Tetsu: "We need to merge back—"

Aka: "How?!"

They try. Reach for each other. Nothing happens.

The cores are SEPARATE now. Permanently.

Aka: "...Fuck."

Tetsu: "This can't be happening—"

Aka: (standing, testing his body) "It already happened."

Tetsu: "We need to FIX this—"

Aka: "Why?"

Tetsu: "What do you mean WHY?! We're supposed to be—"

Aka: "I'm TIRED of being stuck in your head. Maybe this is BETTER."

Tetsu: "You can't be serious—"

Aka: (walking away) "I'm finally FREE. Yeah. This is better."

Tetsu: "Where are you GOING?!"

Aka: "Anywhere that's not HERE."

Gone.

Tetsu: (alone, staring at his hands) "...What have I done?"
This scene needs:
•	✅ Sudden (no warning)
•	✅ Violent (painful, chaotic)
•	✅ Irreversible (can't just "merge back")
•	✅ Emotional (horror/confusion/fear)
•	✅ Sets up their separation arc
________________________________________
3. HANDLING YOUR FEARS - STRATEGIC APPROACH
Fear: Too similar to existing anime Solution: The RELATIONSHIP is unique. Lean into that. No other anime has "brothers who are the same person but choose to be different people."
Fear: Twist won't land Solution: Don't NEED a conspiracy twist. The emotional beats ARE the twist. The shock is "they STAY separate" not "they were always ___"
Fear: Characters won't feel real Solution: Give them CONTRADICTIONS. Tetsu wants to save people but freezes. Aka claims not to care but protects Tetsu. Real people are contradictory.
Fear: Action won't be cool enough Solution: Each fight needs a PURPOSE. Not just "cool moves" but CHARACTER revealed through combat. Tetsu's foresight = his analytical nature. Aka's momentum = his relentless drive.
Fear: Emotion won't hit hard enough Solution: EARN the emotional moments. Build relationships FIRST, then break them. Make us CARE before you hurt us.
________________________________________
4. THE "MATTERED TO THE WORLD" CORE
This is EVERYTHING. This drives both of them.
Tetsu's Path:
•	Prove he matters through HEROISM
•	Save people, earn respect, be REMEMBERED
•	"I'll matter because I made the world BETTER"
Aka's Path:
•	Prove he matters through FREEDOM
•	Live intensely, take what he wants, be UNFORGETTABLE
•	"I'll matter because I REFUSED to be ignored"
The Parallel:
•	Both are terrified of being NOBODY
•	Both watched peers succeed while they stagnated
•	Both want LEGACY
•	Just different methods
The Climax (Eventually):
•	Both realize: They ALREADY mattered
•	To each other. To their team. To the people they affected.
•	Not through destiny or bloodline
•	Through CHOICE
