CORE TRAITS:
•	Experienced, pragmatic, protective
•	War-weary but still fighting
•	Father figure to younger Resolvers
•	Strict but fair leader
•	Hides emotions (military discipline, cracks occasionally)
•	"Mission first, but bring everyone home"
QUIRKS:
•	Drinks coffee constantly (always has thermos)
•	Writes reports meticulously (bureaucracy master)
•	Quotes old military sayings
•	Checks on team outside missions
•	Terrible at modern technology (flip phone user)
•	Plays shogi (strategic mind even at rest)
•	Doesn't sleep much (nightmares from past)
________________________________________
BACKSTORY:
•	Natural Resolve user (awakened age 20)
•	Military special forces background (before Resolvers existed)
•	Lost entire squad 10 years ago (survivor's guilt)
•	Only one who survived that mission
•	Swore to never lose another team
•	Requested assignment training new Resolvers
•	Sees potential in Tetsu specifically
•	"You remind me of someone I couldn't save" (refers to former teammate)
________________________________________
KUROSAWA LINEAGE TRAIT:
"PERSISTENT WILL"
•	Resolve recovers faster than normal users
•	Can fight longer without exhaustion
•	Abilities last longer/cost less to maintain
•	High stamina baseline
________________________________________
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION: "LAST LINE"
Type: Aura-based Enhancement
Conviction: "I am the last line of defense. Last lines do NOT break."
________________________________________
HOW IT WORKS:
DESPERATION POWER:
•	Takeshi's strength is inversely tied to his team's condition
•	The WORSE the situation, the STRONGER he becomes
•	Not conscious choice - activates automatically when team is threatened
VISUAL:
•	Golden aura appears around him
•	Intensity increases with desperation level
•	Eyes glow gold when aura is active
•	Ground cracks under his feet from pressure
•	Air feels HEAVY around him (oppressive presence)
________________________________________
POWER STAGES:
STAGE 1: FULL STRENGTH TEAM
•	No aura visible
•	Fights at base Grade 2 level
•	Normal capabilities
STAGE 2: TEAM INJURED (1-2 members down)
•	Faint golden aura appears
•	1.5x power increase
•	Noticeably stronger/faster
•	"I've got this. Fall back."
STAGE 3: TEAM CRITICAL (3-4 members down/severely injured)
•	Bright golden aura (visible from distance)
•	2x power increase
•	Can fight multiple Grade 2 opponents simultaneously
•	"Get them out of here. NOW."
STAGE 4: LAST MAN STANDING (Team down or evacuated)
•	FINAL BULWARK activated
•	Aura EXPLODES (blinding, battlefield shakes)
•	3x power increase
•	Can temporarily fight Grade 1 opponents
•	"I'm the last line. And last lines DON'T BREAK."
________________________________________
ABILITIES:
1. GUARDIAN'S STAND (Passive - All Stages)
•	When protecting something/someone behind him
•	Becomes UNMOVABLE (cannot be pushed, thrown, knocked down)
•	Literally plants himself
•	"You'll have to go through me."
2. PROTECTIVE AURA (Stage 2+)
•	Golden aura extends behind him (cone-shaped)
•	Area behind him becomes SAFE ZONE
•	Attacks can't pass through his aura to reach allies
•	Wider at Stage 4 (can protect larger area)
3. DESPERATE STRIKE (Stage 3+)
•	Single devastating attack
•	Channels all accumulated power into one blow
•	Usually enough to eliminate one major threat
•	Costs significant Resolve
4. FINAL BULWARK (Stage 4 Only - Signature)
•	Ultimate form of Last Line
•	For 60 seconds: 
o	Nearly invincible (can tank Grade 1 attacks)
o	Strength rivals Grade 1 temporarily
o	Cannot be moved or stopped
o	Pain completely ignored
•	After 60 seconds: Collapses (completely exhausted)
•	Can only use ONCE per major battle
5. RALLYING PRESENCE (Passive)
•	Even when injured, his presence steadies allies
•	Team fights better when he's standing
•	"If the Captain's still up, we can win"
•	Psychological warfare (enemies know he gets stronger)
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
•	Defensive Anchor: Holds position, protects team
•	Last Stand Specialist: Shines in desperate situations
•	Leadership Fighter: Directs team while fighting
•	Sacrifice Plays: Will take hits meant for others
Weakness:
•	At FULL team strength, he's just "good" (not exceptional)
•	Needs desperation to access peak power
•	Exhausts completely after Final Bulwark
•	Emotionally driven (guilt over past failures affects him)
________________________________________
STORY ROLE:
Training Arc:
•	Head instructor at Tenjin Academy
•	Tough but supportive mentor
•	Sees something special in Tetsu (dual-core fascinates him)
•	Pushes students hard (prepares them for reality)
Division 7:
•	Leads with calm authority
•	Father figure to rookies (Tetsu, Kaito, Sara)
•	Best friends with Jiro (old military buddy)
•	Trusts Ren completely (his right hand)
•	Bonds with Tetsu specifically (mentor/father relationship)
Character Arc:
•	Starts overprotective (haunted by past squad's death)
•	Learns to trust team's strength
•	Jiro's death breaks him (loses his best friend)
•	Nearly gives up (survivor's guilt returns)
•	Team refuses to let him quit
•	Final arc: Passes torch to Tetsu (recommends him for Captain)
•	Survives, retires or moves to administrative/instructor role
Key Relationships:
•	Tetsu: Sees him as son/successor
•	Jiro: Best friend, brother-in-arms, his death is devastating
•	Ren: Trusts her with his life, work wife energy
•	Rookies: Protective, wants them to live the life his old squad couldn't
________________________________________
KEY SCENES:
Establishing Character (Early):
Training exercise. Students struggling.

Takeshi: (drinking coffee, calm) "You're all going to die."

Students: "What?!"

Takeshi: "Out there, when it's real. If you fight like this, you're dead."

Kaito: "That's harsh—"

Takeshi: "Reality is harsh. I'm just honest."

Tetsu: "So what do we do?"

Takeshi: (small smile) "You get better. Or you quit. Those are your options."

He walks away.

Sara: (muttering) "He's an asshole."

Takeshi: (without turning) "I heard that. And yes, I am. Because I want you to LIVE."
Showing His Power (Mid-Story):
Mission goes wrong. Division 7 ambushed.

Multiple Grade 2 enemies. Team getting overwhelmed.

Ren: "Captain, we need to retreat—"

Takeshi: (golden aura flickering) "Not yet."

Jiro: "We're outnumbered five to one—"

Takeshi: (aura intensifying as team gets injured) "Then I'll even the odds."

Sara goes down. Aura brightens.

Kaito gets hit hard. Aura BLAZES.

Takeshi: (Stage 3 active, eyes glowing) "RUN. I'll hold them."

Tetsu: "We're not leaving you—"

Takeshi: "That's an ORDER, Resolver."

Team hesitates.

Takeshi: (Final Bulwark activating) "I said GO!"

Aura EXPLODES. Golden light floods battlefield.

Enemies freeze (instinctive fear).

Takeshi: (standing alone, unmovable) "You want them? Come through ME."

[Team escapes. Takeshi holds the line for 60 seconds. Barely survives.]
After Jiro's Death (Emotional):
Aftermath of Sanctum battle. Jiro dead.

Takeshi in his office. Staring at Jiro's file.

Tetsu enters.

Tetsu: "Captain..."

Takeshi: (hollow voice) "I let another one die."

Tetsu: "You couldn't have—"

Takeshi: "He was RIGHT THERE. I should've been faster."

Tetsu: "He made his choice—"

Takeshi: "I'M THE CAPTAIN. I'm supposed to bring everyone HOME."

Silence.

Tetsu: "...You can't save everyone."

Takeshi: "I know. I KNOW that. Doesn't make it hurt less."

Tetsu: "Jiro wouldn't want you to give up."

Takeshi: (bitter laugh) "Jiro would tell me to stop being dramatic and get back to work."

Tetsu: "Then let's get back to work."

Takeshi: "...Yeah. Yeah, okay."

Stands up. Tired but resolute.

Takeshi: "For Jiro."

Tetsu: "For Jiro."
