________________________________________
RESOLVE MANIFESTATION: "SPIDER'S THEOREM"
Type: Dominion (Territory/Control)
Conviction: "I control the battlefield through perfect positioning. Every piece has its place."
________________________________________
HOW IT WORKS:
TACTICAL WEB:
•	Creates invisible energy threads (like spider silk)
•	Threads connect between surfaces/people
•	Can manipulate positions through threads
•	Turns battlefield into controllable web
VISUAL:
•	Threads are INVISIBLE normally
•	When Resolve is focused: Faint silver shimmer (only she sees clearly)
•	When pulled/activated: Brief flash of silver light
•	Creates geometric patterns across battlefield
•	Like a 3D spider web mapped onto environment
________________________________________
ABILITIES:
1. WEB SETUP (Foundation)
•	Touches surfaces/people to anchor threads
•	Can place up to 20 anchor points simultaneously
•	Threads connect anchors automatically (AI-like optimization)
•	Range: 30 meter radius
•	Setup takes 10-30 seconds (depending on complexity)
2. POSITION CONTROL (Primary Ability)
•	Can PULL on threads to: 
o	Move people/objects
o	Redirect attacks
o	Restrict movement
o	Create barriers
•	Pull strength: Can move up to 200kg
•	Multiple threads on same target = stronger pull
3. TACTICAL REPOSITION (Signature)
•	Can SWAP two anchored targets' positions instantly
•	"Rook takes bishop" chess-style
•	Useful for: 
o	Saving wounded allies (swap with teammate)
o	Repositioning fighters (put bruiser in front, support in back)
o	Disrupting enemy formations (swap their positions)
•	5-second cooldown between swaps
•	Max range: Within her web
4. THREAD NETWORK
•	Can "see" through her web
•	Senses vibrations/movements along threads
•	Knows exact position of everything connected
•	Essentially has full battlefield awareness
5. CONSTRAINT WEB
•	Wraps threads around target (like cocoon)
•	Restricts movement progressively
•	More threads = stronger binding
•	Can immobilize fully if enough threads
•	Target can break free with sufficient force (Grade 1+ can escape)
6. TRIPWIRE
•	Sets threads as traps
•	When enemy crosses: Thread activates (pulls, alerts, or restricts)
•	Can create maze of invisible tripwires
•	Forces enemies into predictable paths
7. COLLAPSE (Ultimate)
•	Pulls ALL threads toward center simultaneously
•	Everything connected gets DRAGGED to focal point
•	Creates massive clustered pileup
•	Enemies crash into each other
•	Allies can brace/resist pull if warned
•	Exhausts her completely (ends web, needs reset)
________________________________________
COMBAT STYLE:
•	Battlefield Controller: Manipulates positions constantly
•	Setup Fighter: Needs time to establish web (vulnerable at start)
•	Team Coordinator: Directs allies through optimal positions
•	Strategic Manipulator: Thinks 3-5 moves ahead
Strengths:
•	Complete battlefield control (in her web)
•	Team synergy (enables everyone)
•	Information gathering (senses through threads)
•	Crowd control specialist
Weaknesses:
•	Setup time required (can't instant-activate)
•	Limited to web radius (if fight moves, loses advantage)
•	Threads can be cut/broken (Grade 1+ can power through)
•	Vulnerable if rushed before setup complete
________________________________________
STORY ROLE:
Training Arc:
•	Instructor for tactical courses at Tenjin Academy
•	Teaches positioning, awareness, teamwork
•	Respects Tetsu's analytical mind
•	Clashes with Kaito (he's too impulsive)
•	Values Sara's tactical thinking
Division 7:
•	Vice-Captain (second-in-command)
•	Handles logistics, planning, briefings
•	Takeshi's right hand (work wife energy)
•	Trusts him completely, he trusts her
•	More emotionally distant than Takeshi (less "parental")
•	But deeply cares about team (shows through actions, not words)
Character Arc:
•	Starts treating team as "chess pieces" (useful tools)
•	Learns they're PEOPLE (not just tactical assets)
•	Jiro's death devastates her (loses emotional control first time)
•	Blames herself (should've positioned him better)
•	Nearly becomes reckless in revenge
•	Team pulls her back
•	Final form: Still tactical but PROTECTIVE (balance)
Key Relationships:
•	Takeshi: Work partner, complete trust, mutual respect
•	Jiro: Friend, his death breaks her composure
•	Tetsu: Respects his mind, teaches him tactical thinking
•	Rookies: Tough love approach, but protective
•	Aka: Distrusts him (too unpredictable for her plans)
________________________________________
KEY SCENES:
Establishing Character:
Training exercise. Students bunched together.

Ren: "You're all going to die."

Kaito: "What?! We're doing fine—"

Ren: "You're clustered. One area attack kills all of you."

Sara: "So what do we do?"

Ren: "Spread out. Maintain sight lines. Create overlapping coverage."

Tetsu: (analyzing) "Triangle formation?"

Ren: (small nod) "Good. You're thinking. The rest of you should try it."

Kaito: "Hey—"

Ren: "Statistically speaking, you die first. Too aggressive, poor positioning."

Kaito: "...Rude."

Ren: "Accurate."
Showing Her Power:
Division 7 ambushed in warehouse.

Enemies surrounding them.

Ren: (calmly touching walls, floor, crates) "Give me ten seconds."

Takeshi: "You've got five."

Ren: (faster) "Then talk faster."

Web established. Silver threads shimmer into place.

Ren: "Done. Captain, front. Jiro, left flank. Kaito, right. Sara, elevated position—"

PULLS Sara's thread. She's yanked to top of crate.

Sara: "Whoa—"

Ren: "Shoot from there. Tetsu, analyze their pattern. Daichi, stay center."

Enemy charges Daichi.

Ren: (pulls thread) 

Jiro SWAPS positions with Daichi instantly.

Enemy hits Jiro instead (who tanks it easily).

Jiro: "Thanks for the dance."

Ren: "Focus."

[Perfect orchestrated battle. Every position optimal. Team wins easily.]

Takeshi: (after) "Show off."

Ren: (small smile) "Just doing my job."
After Jiro's Death:
Sanctum assault. Jiro dead.

Ren standing over his body. Face blank.

Tetsu: "Ren—"

Ren: "I positioned him there."

Tetsu: "It's not your fault—"

Ren: "I POSITIONED HIM THERE. I chose that spot. I said 'Jiro, front line.' And now he's DEAD."

Tetsu: "He made his own choice—"

Ren: (voice cracking) "I'm the tactical lead. Positioning is MY job. And I put him where he DIED."

Tetsu: "Ren—"

Ren: (tears streaming, still blank expression) "Statistically speaking... I should've seen this outcome. I should've calculated the risk. I should've—"

Breaks down completely. First time showing full emotion.

Tetsu: (holding her) "It's not your fault."

Ren: (sobbing) "Then why does it feel like it is?"
Final Arc - Growth:
Major battle. Team in danger.

Old Ren would say: "Kaito, front. Sara, back. Optimal positions."

New Ren says: "Kaito, can you hold front?"

Kaito: "Yeah."

Ren: "Then do it. I'll cover you."

Uses web to SUPPORT, not just COMMAND.

Pulls enemy away from Kaito when he's struggling.

Swaps Daichi in to heal him.

Creates barrier with threads.

Tetsu: (noticing) "You're fighting differently."

Ren: "They're not pieces. They're people."

Tetsu: "Took you long enough."

Ren: (small smile) "Better late than never."
