PROS:
✅ Explains the dual-core uniqueness - Not random, tied to past ✅ Adds tragic backstory - Brothers died together, reborn together ✅ Potential for deep lore - Past life enemies, unfinished business ✅ Emotional weight - They were ACTUAL brothers before ✅ Justifies their bond - Not just "split personality," REAL relationship from past
CONS:
❌ Undermines the core uniqueness you wanted - You said "no one has written characters like this" but past-life reincarnation IS common in anime ❌ Removes the "same person, different paths" tension - If they were always separate people, the internal conflict becomes external (just reincarnation) ❌ Adds destiny/fate element - Takes away their agency ("we were meant to be this way") ❌ Complicates the "proving we matter" theme - They already mattered (in past life as strong fighters) ❌ Feels like Naruto/Bleach/standard reincarnation trope - Loses the psychological uniqueness
