•	✅ Keeps Tetsu as ONE person split into TWO
•	✅ Explains the dual-core (two fragments, one body)
•	✅ Adds backstory without removing agency
•	✅ They're not "the brothers reborn" - they're NEW people with OLD echoes
•	✅ Maintains psychological tension (still internal conflict)
The reveal:
Aka: "I've been having dreams. Memories that aren't mine."

Tetsu: "Me too. Battles. Someone beside me—"

Aka: "A brother."

Tetsu: "...What?"

Ancient records show: The Fractured One had a twin brother.

They died together. Their Resolve scattered.

Tetsu carries fragments of BOTH.

That's why the split was so perfect.

Not reincarnation. INHERITANCE.

Tetsu: "So we're not them."

Aka: "No. We're us. But they're... inside us. Part of us."

Tetsu: "Does that change anything?"

