•	Clear explanation for WHY Tetsu specifically
•	Epic backstory and lore depth
•	Parallel to successful dynamics (Gojo/Geto, Naruto/Sasuke)
•	Bigger emotional stakes
HERE'S WHAT I THINK YOU'RE ACTUALLY STRUGGLING WITH:
You want the PSYCHOLOGICAL UNIQUENESS of the split personality
BUT you also want the EPIC SCALE of the reincarnation tragedy
AND YOU CAN HAVE BOTH.
________________________________________
MY SOLUTION: THE HYBRID THAT ACTUALLY WORKS
THE SETUP:
Current Timeline (What Audiences See First):
•	Tetsu Mikage, 21 years old
•	During The Collision, he splits into Host and Other
•	They appear to be one soul fractured into two perspectives
•	Classic split personality dynamic
•	THIS IS ACTS 1-2
The Truth (Mid-Story Revelation):
The Collision didn't CREATE the split.
It AWAKENED something that was always there.
Past Life Reality:
800 years ago:
•	Two brothers (not named Tetsu/Aka - different identities)
•	Both legendary Resolve users
•	Fought together, inseparable
•	Betrayed and killed by their closest friend/rival
•	Died together, swearing they'd find each other again
Their souls:
•	Reincarnated across centuries
•	Usually born separately as different people
•	Sometimes found each other, sometimes didn't
•	But always DRAWN to each other
Tetsu's Generation:
The Error:
•	Both souls were supposed to reincarnate as SEPARATE people
•	The Collision disrupted the natural cycle
•	Both souls got compressed into ONE body (current Tetsu)
•	Creating the "split"
So the truth is:
•	Host ≠ just "cautious Tetsu"
•	Other ≠ just "reckless Tetsu"
•	They're TWO DIFFERENT SOULS that have been BROTHERS across lifetimes
•	Forced into one body by cosmic accident
•	Don't remember past lives (yet)
________________________________________
WHY THIS VERSION IS SUPERIOR:
KEEPS YOUR UNIQUE CONCEPT:
✅ Still starts as psychological split-personality story ✅ Tetsu struggles with "who am I?" ✅ Internal conflict made external ✅ Audiences experience it as ONE person fighting himself
ADDS THE EPIC SCALE:
✅ Past-life backstory exists (epic lore) ✅ Reincarnation cycle adds depth ✅ Connection to ancient conflicts ✅ Explains WHY Tetsu specifically
CREATES DEVASTATING MID-STORY TWIST:
✅ "We're not one person split... we're two people trapped" ✅ Identity crisis MULTIPLIED ✅ "Who am I if I'm not even ME?" ✅ Reframes entire story retroactively
