WHY THIS VERSION IS ACTUALLY BRILLIANT
WHAT MAKES IT UNIQUE:
1. THE BINDING TECHNIQUE
This is the genius part:
•	The Other didn't just reincarnate randomly
•	He created a FAIL-SAFE before dying
•	"If my brother is ever in danger from Resolve energy, I'll return to protect him"
•	Like a guardian curse/blessing
2. THE FORCED PARTNERSHIP
•	Tetsu is living his own life
•	The Collision triggers the ancient technique
•	Suddenly his dead brother from 800 years ago is INSIDE him
•	Neither asked for this
•	But they're stuck together
3. THE MORALLY GRAY ENEMY
•	Past-life nemesis wasn't evil
•	Was fighting for something he believed was right
•	Tetsu and The Other had to fight their FRIEND
•	"Sometimes the right thing feels wrong"
•	Tragic choice, not good vs evil
