HOW THIS ACTUALLY PLAYS OUT
THE REVEAL SEQUENCE:
Mid-Story (Act 3):
Aka having dreams. Memories surfacing.
Aka: "I remember... dying."
Tetsu: "What?"
Aka: "And I remember YOU. Your face. Different name. Same eyes."
Tetsu: "That's impossible—"
Aka: "I died first. You were screaming my name. And I— I couldn't protect you."
The Investigation:
Ancient texts mention a legendary technique:
•	"Soul Tether" or "Blood Binding" or "Brother's Oath"
•	Forbidden Resolve technique
•	Allows one soul to bind itself to another across lifetimes
•	"When the bound soul faces Resolve catastrophe, the tethered soul returns"
Tetsu: "You... you BOUND yourself to me? 800 years ago?"
Aka: "To protect you. So you'd never be alone when it mattered."
Tetsu: "But I didn't ASK for this—"
Aka: "You were my BROTHER. I wasn't going to let you face the next life alone."
The Past-Life Memory:
FLASHBACK - 800 years ago:
The Other (different name, same soul) dying on battlefield.
Younger brother (Tetsu's past-self) alive but injured.
Enemy approaching.
The Other: (coughing blood) "I won't... leave you..."
Uses forbidden technique. Burns his own soul as fuel.
The Other: "No matter how many lives... I'll find you... I'll protect you..."
Technique activates. Soul fragments bind to younger brother.
The Other: "We're brothers... forever now..."
Dies.
Enemy kills younger brother moments later.
But the technique is DONE. Across all future lifetimes, they're connected.
