THE EMOTIONAL CORE
The Other's Perspective:
"I bound myself to you to PROTECT you.
I wanted to save you from being alone.
But now I'm the one causing you pain.
I'm the voice that makes you doubt.
I'm the reason you can't be normal.
I tried to be your shield... and I became your burden."
Tetsu's Perspective:
"You sacrificed everything to protect me.
Across 800 years, you kept your promise.
But I didn't ASK for this.
I didn't ASK to have you in my head.
I didn't ASK to relive your war.
...But you're my brother.
And I'm not giving up on you."
________________________________________
THE ARCH-NEMESIS SITUATION
Here's where it gets INTERESTING:
Past Life:
•	Three friends/comrades
•	Philosophical split
•	Nemesis believes in extreme order/control (like Sanctum)
•	Brothers believe in freedom/choice
•	"You're going to destroy everything" vs "You're going to enslave everyone"
•	Neither is wrong, both are right
•	Tragic battle, all die
Present Day Options:
OPTION A: Nemesis also reincarnated (but separately)
•	Could be someone they DON'T recognize initially
•	Memories return for all three
•	Same conflict plays out again
•	"Can we break the cycle this time?"
OPTION B: Nemesis's IDEOLOGY reincarnated (The Sanctum)
•	The actual person is dead
•	But their philosophy survived across 800 years
•	The Sanctum carries on their mission
•	"We're fighting our friend's LEGACY, not our friend"
OPTION C: Nemesis is ALIVE and orchestrating everything
•	Never died, found immortality
•	Has been waiting 800 years for the brothers to return
•	"Finally... I can finish what we started"
•	Sees their return as destiny/fate
MY RECOMMENDATION: OPTION B - Fighting ideology, not person
Why: More thematically rich. Not "beat the bad guy," but "do we repeat the same mistakes?"
________________________________________
ANSWERING THE CORE QUESTIONS
Q: Why did the split happen to Tetsu specifically?
A: The Other bound himself to Tetsu 800 years ago. When The Collision hit, the ancient technique activated, pulling The Other's soul into Tetsu's body.
Q: Why are they in ONE body instead of separate?
A: The binding technique wasn't meant to create a separate body. It was meant to MERGE their souls for protection. "If I'm inside you, I can protect you from within."
Q: What was The Other's arch-nemesis fighting for?
A: Order, control, safety through structure. Genuinely believed freedom would destroy the world. Not evil, just opposite philosophy.
Q: Is the nemesis alive now?
A: Up to you - but I recommend their IDEOLOGY is alive (Sanctum) rather than the actual person.
________________________________________
HOW THIS CHANGES THE STORY
ACTS 1-2: (No Change)
•	Everything we built stays
•	Split personality dynamic
•	Learning powers, building relationships
•	Audiences don't know the past-life connection yet
ACT 3: The Revelation
•	Memories start surfacing
•	The binding technique is discovered
•	Truth revealed: The Other isn't a split personality, he's a BOUND SOUL
•	Identity crisis: "Which one of us is the real Tetsu?"
ACT 4: The Ideology Conflict
•	Sanctum's goals mirror the past-life nemesis
•	"We're fighting the same war 800 years later"
•	Brothers must choose: repeat the past or break the cycle
ACT 5: The Resolution
•	Unlike past lives where they died together
•	This time they CHOOSE how to live
•	Maybe they stay bound, maybe they find a way to separate safely
•	"You protected me for 800 years. Now let me protect you."
