THE SEPARATION - RECONTEXTUALIZED
When they physically separate (Ch 98-100):
Original idea: Cores just split during battle.
NEW CONTEXT: The binding technique is BREAKING.
The Other's soul, bound for 800 years, is finally being RELEASED.
Not because they hate each other.
Because the technique was never meant to be permanent.
The Scene:
Mid-battle. Cores overloading.
Aka: "Something's wrong—"
Tetsu: "What's happening?!"
Ancient technique unraveling. 800-year-old binding shattering.
Aka: "The technique... it's breaking..."
Tetsu: "What does that mean?!"
Aka: "It means... I'm finally free."
Tetsu: "No— we need to—"
Aka: "I was never supposed to be inside you forever. Just until you were safe."
Tetsu: "You CAN'T leave—"
Aka: "I'm not leaving. I'm just... finally becoming real."
Golden chains (the binding) visible for first time, BREAKING.
SNAP.
Aka's soul ejected. Forms physical body.
Two people standing where one was.
Aka: (staring at his own hands) "I'm... out."
Tetsu: "You're leaving—"
Aka: "I'm FREE."
Tetsu: "So you're just going to—"
Aka: "I protected you for 800 years. I think I've earned the right to live MY life now."
Walks away.
Tetsu: (devastated) "You promised you'd never leave me alone..."
Aka: (stops, doesn't turn) "You're not alone. You have them." (gestures to Division 7)
"And I'll still be your brother. Just... not your cage."
Gone.
